animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
How to perfectly summarize Venus: "Though she be but little, she is fierce". Venus originally came to us before Thanksgiving as one of the members of the Sunshine Kids litter. Right off the bat, Venus was special. She was quiet and sweet and always expressed gratitude by giving kisses whenever something was done for her. Beautiful in her own way, Venus was passed over several times before being adopted as she wasn't as blonde as her siblings / she looked "too different". Over time, her "mask" has faded but she is as beautiful as ever.

Venus was adopted around the same time as her siblings at around 10 weeks old, but was promptly returned for behavioral problems.... none of which she exhibited prior to adoption. With either a few weeks maturity or just a very different environment, she seemed to shift into a dog who resisited handling quite fervently.

After confirming that her growling at being picked up was not medically related, we put together a program to help build her trust, solidify fair boundries, and associate restraint and handling with positive things.

Venus has come a very long way since returning to our care. She has learned how to express her boundaries and communicate when she doesn't want to be picked up/held, in a calm voice.

Venus does display affection, but on her own terms. She prefers to climb into your lap or sit next to you vs being picked up or placed where you want her. She does respond to her name, sits when asked, and will come to you when called (most of the time). When she wants to say thank you or just let you know she's happy, she will come up to you and wait for you to lean close so she can steal a kiss. She LOVES to run around in the fenced back yard of her foster home and play with all the toys. Venus does not like to be alone. However, while she likes the company of another dog to play with, she is a bit sassy and bossy. Her ideal playmate is a dog that doesn't mind being told what to do.

Venus would thrive in a home without cats or children, a fenced area to play in, and active loving parents who will continue to work with her, show patience, and reassure her that she is safe and loved. She would love to meet any potential dog siblings before deciding on her forever home.

Venus is a smart girl who is crate trained and ready to continue potty training, learn new tricks, and be a permanent part of a family.

Our first step is an application which can be filled out at: www.cvrrescue.org The adoption fee for this dog is $250.00 which helps to cover a portion of the care provided, including: spay/neuter, microchip, heartworm testing, deworming, age appropriate vaccinations: DHLP/P, Bordetella, Rabies, and any medical care received while with CVRR. All animals are on flea/tick and parasite prevention for the duration of foster care. CVRR is a nonprofit organization, we have no paid staff. Applications are reviewed and processed by our volunteers. Please be patient and understand that it takes an average of 7-14 days to process the applications including reference checks and follow-up questions. You can expedite the process by providing accurate phone and email info for all your references. Once your application is approved, we will schedule a meet-and-greet to see if the dog picks you too. If it seems the adoption will be a good match for all, there is an adoption fee and an adoption contract to be signed. The adoption fee helps to cover a portion of the care provided to the animals. By the time of adoption all dogs are spayed/neutered, microchipped, and up to date on vetting. CVRR is a NO KILL rescue organization and we have a LIFETIME COMMITMENT to all of our animals. If for any reason the adoption does not work out the animal is to be returned to CVRR. We will re-evaluate and choose a new home based on the best fit for that particular animal. A note about puppies: Adopters can expect a new puppy to have accidents, chew things they shouldn't, and have other normal energetic puppy issues such as jumping, mouthing, and general youthful naughtiness, until they are trained. If you are having puppy issues please feel free to contact us, we are happy to give you guidance. Because this is a mixed breed we cannot guarantee an adult weight. If your residence has weight restrictions or you are looking for an ideal weight we don't recommend applying for this puppy (you can always check out the adult dogs whose weights we do know).

animal.description: SALUTATIONS! Salutations are greetings; it's my fancy way of saying hello. That was how Charlotte greeted Wilbur in Charlotte's Web, and like that Wilbur, our Wilbur is SOME PIGer, dog! Wilbur is a two year old cutie who has been in a home for the last several months after being found as a stray. According to his former owner, Wilbur has done great with other dogs and has also done fine with young children, generally keeping his distance. Wilbur has been an outside pet, but unlike his porcine namesake who was comfortable in the barnyard, he would prefer a place indoors next to his family in his future home. Wilbur is a timid boy who could use help gaining confidence- a patient, calm home with a confident doggy friend to guide him would be just the ticket! Ask about Wilbur today- we think he's TERRIFIC!

Please contact JoEllen (sagdinfo@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **
Cathy is an adorable 4-month-old Labrador blend who weighs approximately 16 pounds. She has a sweet temperament and is active and playful. She will make a loyal companion.
Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for her entire life (up to 15+ years or more) - not just until her puppy cuteness wears off.
You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropriate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization. Like most puppies, she may chew on anything within her reach to include but not limited to baseboards, shoes, socks, children's toys, electrical cords, plants, etc.
Her adoption fee is $200. This includes her spay surgery, rabies vaccination, Nobivac Canine 1-DAPP vaccinations, Bravecto, Drontal Plus, Tri-Heart Plus Chewable Tablet, 24PetWatch microchip, leash and collar, and a trial offer for 24PetWatch Pet Insurance.
Please be aware that puppies and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.
Please ensure your application is complete before submitting. We do verify property ownership, landlord references, apartment/HOA restrictions, veterinary references, and criminal histories.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.
Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com.
** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and opportunity to enroll in a 30-day trial of pet insurance.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Show stopper alert! 


Stax is a great guy who found himself abandoned by his owners and then confiscated by the local pound in Memphis, TN. Strangely, it is probably the best thing that ever happened to him because now he is a PAWS New England dog and our mission is to find him a perfect home.

Stax is very gentle, young, with smooth brindle fur, and captivating amber eyes. He is sweet, quiet, crate trained, and plays well with others too! 

His favorite activities with his canine pals are playing chase and wrestling. 

Stax also loves to cuddle with his people, have his back scratched, and give lots of kisses.

He is a popular guy so get your application in fast! Stax is ready to rock-n-roll north to his forever home!

Check out his videos! 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vaQaUWUcVpc
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iNWmUvwFRzE 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iNWmUvwFRzE Stax and Babie


Name: Stax
Breed: Plott Hound/Pit Mix
Sex: Male
Age: 2-3 years of age
Weight: 60 lbs
Spayed/Neutered: Yes
Vaccinations: Up to date
Heartworm: Positive, has begun treatment
Microchipped: Yes

BASED ON OUR OBSERVATIONS: 
Good with Children: Over 12
Good with Dogs: Yes
Good with Cats: Unknown

Adoption Fee: $475.00


IMPORTANT INFORMATION:
Interested in a specific dog, please fill out an application if you are interested in a dog. The number of individual inquiries is overwhelming and we are finding it difficult to respond to each one. We cannot guarantee you will receive a timely response.

Paws New England is a rescue, not a shelter, and as such we do not have our dogs housed in one location - they are in foster homes both in New England and in our southern foster homes. If you're interested in a specific dog, please complete a short online application and you will receive a reply within 48 hours so you can ask questions.

At present, if a dog is listed on our website, the dog is considered still available HOWEVER, may have applications that have come in before yours but it's still too early to know if any are a good match; therefore we encourage you to apply.


NOTICE WITH REGARD TO LOCATION OF DOGS: Please note: Paws New England is a foster-based rescue. We do not have a brick and mortar building to house the dogs we rescue. We have found that dogs in foster homes are much more adoptable because they have been observed in a home setting. Dogs listed with Paws New England typically reside in various locations throughout the south (primarily Tennessee, Texas, and Arkansas) and New England (not necessarily in the state of Rhode Island). You will be notified by the adoption coordinator of the location of the dog you are interested in so you have the ability to decide whether to pursue adoption or not.

Dogs transported to New England are done so at a fee of $150.00 paid directly to the transporting company by Paws New England; no additional transport costs are responsibility of adopter. This fee is included in the adoption donation.

Adoption donations cover pre-adoption vet costs (including vaccinations, spay/neuter when age appropriate, and heartworm testing/treatment when necessary), a microchip, and transportation to New England if necessary.

Donations for our young, healthy puppies and dogs support their fellow canines of advanced age or suffering from injuries and abuse whose donations are reduced but whose veterinary costs are typically much higher. We appreciate your understanding that your dog will help others in need.

All known information about the animal is listed above. We do our best to give accurate information, but most of our dogs are rescues and do not come with a known history.

Paws New England abides by the dog importation regulations set forth in the states of MA, CT, NH and RI.

animal.description:
Prancing little princess when I am happy. Sometimes my wiggle butt is so exuberant, I almost tip over. I'm guessing this is quite cute because I notice my foster mom smiling at me all the time! 
Have you heard of zoomies? Well, I have achieved a gold star for zoomie ability. In fact, I love to run a few laps of zoomies in my fosters fenced yard right before I pick the most perfect spot to complete my outside business. 
Classified as a "Timeless Treasure .... (aka. Senior) I am proud of my maturity. Free from puppy shenanigans, I am a wonderful companion. Sharing space with my humans is amazing. I love couch time and simply hanging out together in the house. Other dog companions are totally awesome for me too. My foster sister is the best. She was once a homeless pup too. She inspires me everyday to believe that I can have my own family! 
Being 11, I have experienced a significant amount of life experiences. Some good.... Some I would rather leave in my past. 
I am searching for a home filled with love and kindness. I like a more chill pace to life where I can decide when it's time to run around and be silly. Since I have been let down for so many years, I am initially a bit reserved. Be patient, I will allow you into my world. Be kind, I will work to build new levels of trust. Be ready to offer me a world filled with love, and I will open my heart to you. 
Ps. Remember I love rump rubs and to happy prance. 
Also, consider the world of a difference you could make in my life by choosing to allow me to live the remainder of my days knowing that I am valuable and worthy of being adopted. 
~Love, Mrs. Howell 

Contact Unleashed if you would like to give this Timeless Treasure a chance for the best future ever.

animal.description:
Please reference
www.DefensaAnimalDePuertoRico.org/Adopt
to learn how adoptions work with Defensa & Rescuers.

Bodhi is an adorable 30-pound fox terrier/schnauzer mix who was spotted walking along a road in Rincon all by himself, with sores and ticks covering his body. He is now in a loving foster home and receiving treatment for heartworm. He is doing great! His foster mom says, "Bodhi continues to amaze me with his sweet, affectionate nature. This boy is so grateful and will be an amazing family member for someone once he is healthy. He is a cuddly love bug who would do great with a family or person who is around a lot. Bodhi gets along with other dogs but seems to prefer to have all of the attention for himself. He is mellow and probably doesn't need to have a yard to run in. He would likely be happy having leash walks and an occasional off leash romp in the park. Healthwise, Bodhi is currently undergoing treatment for heart worm but should be ready for adoption around April. He is otherwise healthy, has been vaccinated, and will be neutered on February 1." The vet believes Bodhi is around four years old.

If you are interested in giving this sweetheart a home, please contact Ellen at ellenpberrios@gmail.com or 617-905-8694. Bodhi is available for adoption on- and off-island.

If you don't find the pet you are looking for at Defensa, please consider adopting from another organization helping homeless animals on the island or from one of the high-kill shelters (e.g. Villa Michelle).

Thank you for considering adopting a rescued animal. Learn more about what we do and support our efforts to help the street animals of Puerto Rico at

www.DefensaAnimalDePuertoRico.org

Nosey is such a gentle, calm, tender hearted soul! She is three years old and weighs 68 pounds. 

Nosey loves being around people and ambles contentedly at your side on daily walks. Once she is done, she loves being petted and cuddled. Nosey is so good natured and affectionate and will be such a devoted companion!

She also loves time in the fenced play yard.

Nosey would do best in a home with a medium or larger dog. If you have another dog, we require a meet and greet to ensure compatibility. Nosey would also be fine as the only dog, where she can have you all to herself! She does needs a household without cats.

Nosey can have some separation anxiety, and our staff would be glad to help discuss how to help her with this, including crating Nosey when she is alone.

E-mail animalcontrol@cheathamcountytn.gov for more information!

Please come visit! We are open seven days a week from 9:00 a.m. to 3:30 p.m.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Due to Covid 19 you must have an approved application to visit our facility. You can apply for a dog at www.adoggie4you.org. This pup is approximately 6 years old, weighs 13 pounds and is HW Negative. The adoption fee is $300.00

Cayden and Clifford came to us from a horrific hoarding case in the Rio Grande Valley of Texas. They were kept in a warehouse with over 100 other dogs, deprived of light, food and interaction. They were a mess when they came to us. They were used to fighting for every bite of food and fighting humans that were abusing them.

Cayden and Clifford blossomed under our care. They play with other dogs now and even play with toys. They love the handler's that take care of them and they are no longer terrifed when they are being groomed. Both these dogs have come a long way.

Both Cayden and Clifford were adopted a year ago by a very nice family. Cayden was returned within a week for trying to bite the husband. We suspect it was because he was wearing a uniform. Clifford lasted four months longer. He was doing great, but he tried to bite the husband and he was returned. He did good with the wife and children. Over the last year they both have really become more social and we want to give them another chance to find a family.

If you don't have an abundance of patience and the experience to work with a dog that has been mistreated, please don't apply. These boys need an opportunity to shine.

animal.description:
Contrary to what you might think, Layla is not half bear half wolf, although when she gets excited she does like to give out a ladylike little howl. The only time she might seem a bit bear-ish is when someone tries to take away her rawhide bone, those manners need some work! Otherwise, Layla is a polite older girl, who is potty-trained, walks well on a leash, knows how to sit, and loves to shake hands (especially when she spies some food she wants). She loves kids, but would probably do best in a house with children who are old enough to understand her need for some space and gentleness. She doesn't seem to mind other dogs as long as they follow the not-in-her-face rule. Layla hasn't been observed around cats, but likely wouldn't have the energy to chase them. 

Layla is what they call geriatric, and her body fits that description, however, her spirit is younger than her ten years! She does have some health needs including joint pain, a heart murmur, and poor hearing and eyesight, as well as undergoing treatment for heartworms, but she still has so much life left in her! She loves riding in the car, and gets very excited for her brief walks. If you are looking for a quiet couch potato to be your giant teddy bear, we hope you will give this precious girl a chance!

animal.description:
Are you looking for a big fella with an even bigger heart? This gorgeous boy (about 80 lbs.) is looking to become someone’s BFF. Remi is a very affectionate dog that loves being with his people. He’s gentle and loving, a bit of a couch potato, but ready for a long walk or hike when he’s not chillin’. Although he has lived with other dogs, he does best as an only pet. Unfortunately he is not cat friendly. With humans though, he is sweet and gentle and submissive. Remi would do best in an active home where he is an integral part of the family. He’s not a back yard dog in any sense. He has excellent house manners, is never destructive and completely house broken. He walks well on a leash and rides well in a car. In fact, if you like road trips, Remi would be an excellent travel companion. Like camping?  Remi would love to share your tent. If a part adventurer / part couch potato sounds like your kind of dog, please consider adding Remi to your family.  

Remi is neutered, up to date on vaccinations, microchipped, heartworm negative and current on flea/tick medications.  His adoption fee is $200

animal.description:
*PLEASE NOTE:  We do not adopt out on a first-come/first-serve basis.  Applications are accepted for a puppy and then a home check is scheduled.  If there are multiple applications for a puppy, after all home checks are done, then the puppy is adopted out to the home that is the best fit for that puppy.
***** All breeds listed are a best guess or based on information from our rescue partners and are not guaranteed*****
 
 ******Chicagoland Dog Rescue reserves the right to restrict adoption of a dog to potential adopters who live within a fifty (50) mile radius of Schaumburg, IL *****

Who has the best ears and the most beautiful eyes and is a total softie on the inside? Me! I am the sweetest and most polite girl you will ever meet. I LOVE every person I meet. I will ALWAYS be excited to see you when you come home, or even back into the room after you’ve left for a while! I am good with kids and I am dog friendly. I am a sweet, playful, and curious pup! My hobbies include belly rubs, back scratches, playing with my ball (and other toys), sniffing and running around in the yard, and going for walks. My foster mom says I am awesome on a leash! Bonus: I am already potty trained and crate trained! I know sit, come, and paw. I am working on down and stay. I bet I will learn them soon because I will do anything for a treat, and I am one smart girl. My foster mom tells me all the time what a good girl I am and how quiet I am- she has never heard me bark! I would love to be a part of your family! If you would like to meet me, please send an email or fill out a pre-adoption application and a CDR volunteer will get back to you just as quick as they can!
Cuddles and kisses-Jolie



**The ADOPTION FEE for this pet is $450 which includes getting the puppy/dog up to date on rabies, distemper and bordetella vaccines, fecal test and deworming if necessary, heartworm test, spay or neuter (not including pre-surgical bloodwork) and a microchip. Free access to our weekly training classes is also included for the life of the dog, something no other rescue in the area offers.***

animal.description:
Medical Note: I am Ehrlichia positive. Treatment is 28 days of doxcycyline (an inexpensive antibiotic). The adopter is responsible for treatment of the dog. ODHS does not pay for this treatment. I also have a deformity on my front left paw and am missing a couple toes. I went to a vet, received x-rays, and gave me the all clear. I may need amputation later in the future as I get older, but for now it does not bother me.

Hi my name is Peggy I am about 2 years old and weigh about 35lbs. I love walks and running in the backyard. I was born with what my foster mom calls a special paw. I don’t have all my toes on my left front leg, but it does not slow me down!

I don't mind being the crate, but my foster mama gives me lost of blankets and some music so I don't feel so alone. I really like to lay on my bed around people. I love company! I have great potty manners. I sit or go to the door if I want out (that might not be to go to the bathroom. I might just want to go outside and see the world!)

I am excited to meet new people, but am a little shy at first. Once I know you, I get excited to see you and my tail won’t stop! I love other dogs and want to go meet everyone on a walk. 

I do really well on a leash. My foster mom walks on my right so the leash will not get caught up on my special paw. She also walks in the gravel most of the walk so I can walk in the grass. Walking in the grass helps me be able to walk longer. I can walk on all surfaces, but grass is my favorite. 

I learned how to go up and down stairs and now I can’t stop - they are so much fun! I also am working on sitting on command and I am learning fast! I also don’t bug you while you eat I just lay and rest. 

I do a nice job staying off of most furniture, but love the human big beds and snuggling up. I correct easily so even if I get up somewhere you don’t want I will learn fast. 

I have met a cat. She was mean and tried to swat me and made a horrible hissing sound. I just ignored her and ran away because it was pretty clear she did not want to be friends.,

You can still come adopt me or even join our foster program to help the humans learn all the awesome things about new dogs like me! Learn more on our website! 

Hope to see you soon! 

What breed am I? Mixed mutt! ODHS does not breed label (unless there’s official paperwork), as studies show it is nearly impossible to tell the exact breed of each dog based off of their appearance.

flea/tick prevention, heart worm prevention, vet examination. 

ALL OUR DOGS JOURNEY BEGINS IN TENNESSEE 

We have a twice monthly trip to the Chicago area to bring the adopted dogs to their new families. The next transport date for the adopted dogs is Friday, January 22, 2021.  

Our primary source of funding comes from this adoption donation. This donation allows us to rescue other dogs in danger of being put to sleep, injured or sick dogs and dogs that have never known the comfort of a home.

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Chowder and I one handsome boy.  I am approximately five months old.  My humans think I may be a Labrador/Staffordshire terrier mix. I am a little shy, but its going to be short lived.  I just need to get out and experience the world.  A good Samaritan took me and my three littermates in after our mom was run over by a vehicle.  We were only eight weeks old when we lost our mother.  The nice lady did not have permission to have us in her apartment, so she kept us hidden.  She taught us to use potty pads and really spent a lot of time loving us.  After we grew, it was impossible to hide us anymore and she was forced to ask for help.   
  
Homeless days are behind us now and I am looking for a new place to call home.  I am looking for an endless supply of fun toys and doggie treats!

I am learning to walk on a leash and its coming right along. 
 
I am neutered, microchipped and up to date on vaccines.
I’m in Seattle now!

If you are looking for a big old teddy bear of a dog, look no further! My name is Buster I am a very sweet extra large dog who loves just about everyone I meet. animal.description:
Hi! I’m Khaleesi a 7 year old sweet and soft pitbull mix looking for a home with a doggy playmate. I have had a tough life but I am resilient. I was bounced around for my whole life and have had approx 3-4 homes. I was given up each time at no fault of my own.  All of my human owners were not settled and I was not a part of their forever plan. Even still I love humans. I love affection and I am a very good natured and have a sweet temperament. 

I am good with dogs who like to play and who are also behaved. I am sort of a parrot. I am fresh with fresh dogs , good with good dogs, and submissive with submissive /laid back dogs. I would love a doggy friend to play with. I like to play, and have a up beat play style. 

I like laid back, submissive, sweet dogs. I tire out quick and would prefer someone who likes to play but isn’t hyper. Hyper or rowdy would be too much for me and work me up!

I have never met kids but I most likely would be good with older kids and teens. I am not aggressive in any way but am excited when I am doing something new. So older kids are probably better for me. We would have to see with your kids !

I don’t like cats so I can’t live with cats.

I am spayed, microchipped and up to date on vaccines. I am totally healthy and have no health concerns at my young age of 7. 

As a pre senior I want someone who is dedicated to loving me through my life and who will be invested in caring for me through my later years.

To apply to adopt fill out our app https://www.secondchanceranchrescue.com/apply-to-adopt

animal.description:
Lucca was a holiday surprise that was born into rescue after his Mama was saved from a euthanasia list in Texas. His mom is a gorgeous, full golden retriever who had a little oopsie with an unknown Texas fella. So far, little Lucca has jet black, thick, soft fur with dots of white on his paws, chin, and chest. Lucca is a stout little guy, weighing in at 5 lbs at just three weeks old (!) so we anticipate him being a big boy when he's full grown. Lucca is learning about life as a happy, healthy puppy and getting lots of snuggles with his foster family. *Please note - As an only pup, Lucca's ideal home will be a multi-dog household. This will help Lucca to learn important socialization skills that he would otherwise be learning through interactions with littermates.

The suggested adoption donation for Lucca is $450. We are a 501c3 organization which means that your donation may be TAX DEDUCTIBLE. Your donation goes toward the high cost of veterinary care for our animals in rescue, as well as providing supportive services to animals in homes. 

Information about the adoption process: All adoptions require a completed ADOPTION APPLICATION. Once your application is approved, we will put you in touch with the dogs foster to see if you and the pet are a good match. If so, we will arrange a meeting for you and the pet. The adoptions for all of our animals will take place in the Omaha, NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver. 

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dogs needs. If you and the dog are not a good match, we will help you select another dog, or we will keep your approved application on file for 6 months. 

To learn about Muddy Paws Second Chance Rescue or donate to our animals, please visit our website at MuddyPawsSecondChanceRescue.com or our Facebook Page.

animal.description:
Hello, my name is Hamish. I am an approximately 8 year old neutered male Tub of Love! I am looking for my special someone to let me cuddle with them and watch Netflix during this next phase of the pandemic! I am a mature boy so I do all of my " "business" outside, love walks, eating my meals and treats, but most of all I love to spend time with humans. I come when called, have learned sit, wait for my turn to eat and wait patiently at the door to go out. I will either sleep in MY bed or will gladly sleep with you in yours.

I have heartworm so my rescue group has been kind enough to pay for my treatment at the vet. I am done with the first phase of the antibiotics and will be starting one shot on January 21 with 2 more at the end of February. I heard it is tough on a guy like me, I will probably want to sleep alot and just go outside to go to the bathroom. It's not hard to keep a couch potato like me quiet, though, so that is good news!

If you have a home with no other dogs living there, to steal my thunder ( or food) would you consider fostering me and then adopting me when my treatment is done? I promise to love you SO much!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.MAYA and Wylie

are sweet, docile, and slightly timid. Maya is a Papillon mix and Wylia Is an Italian greyhound and Chihuahua mix. they are both approximately 1 year of age. Maya has a medium length coat and she may have some dachshund in her. Wylie has a shorter coat and a sweet face of black and tan. Wylie came accompanied by her puppy Beckett (who has been adopted) The girls were rescued from a 20 dog hoarding home. They came to us with 3 other dogs. Maya and Wylie have been slowly been coming around, will eat out of my hand and are seeking out attention now. We want the girls to have a yard since they are not yet leash trained and this will help them go potty safely as they become accustomed to leads and harnesses.

Both girls needs an adult only home with people who have the time, commitment, and EXPERIENCE with shy dogs or rescued dogs. a yard and time to spend with dogs. They will do wonderfully from with a work from home, retired, or home most of the time couple. They need a child-free home as they are not accustomed to children

Both girls are just so sweet and just want to be someone's lapdog and will be very loving dogs with Time, Patience, and Love. Maya and Wylie have been transitioned to Raw and Human grade dog foods. The owner must commit to staying with this high-quality diet. Rompin Paws will educate the adopters in species-specific feeding and care

animal.description:
Tuxedo is a one and a half year old spitz mix. He currently weighs 19 lbs and is working on gaining a couple more. Tuxedo is shy (at first), but loves fiercely. He is a perfect work from home companion. He loves nothing more than to relax in a room with his humans and getting an occasional head scratch. Because he loves his humans so much, he has some separation anxiety when they leave. Tuxedo has been working on building his confidence to overcome this. He has already improved by leaps and bounds because he is so eager to please. Tuxedo would benefit from someone that is willing to continue to train and work on his confidence. He is potty trained. He does not like being in a crate but can be enticed into one with a kong toy full of tasty treats. Tuxedo is learning how to have fun with dog toys and his other dog playmates. Tuxedo has also been great living with a small child. He also is a great walking buddy and gets so excited when he sees his leash.

PLEASE READ: Please read all information about this pet provided below. If you are interested in adopting this pet, please fill out an application at https://www.hopeanimalshelter.net/petfinder. This pet is not located at our shelter. We are doing adoptions by appointment only at this time, so please fill out an application to start the process. Adoption fees range from $150-$240 (depending on age) and all adoption fees include spay/neuter, age appropriate vaccinations, and microchip with registration. Please email us at hopefostersaz@gmail.com to inquire about availability or for any other questions.

animal.description:
Hello! I'm alpine. I am a 6 year old boy who is ready to find my forever home. I'm young, athletic, and tons of fun! I can be a lot to handle on leash if I haven't gotten a lot of play time that day. A fenced in yard where I can run and play would be best for me. My dream home would be a place that has lots of room indoors for me to take naps, and lots of room outdoors as well for running and jumping around! In terms of other pets, I seem to be friendly with other dogs, but can become frustrated when I cant get to them. It is unknown how I do with cats or small kids. Bring in your older,  10 years old and up, respectful children for a meet and greet. I can be jumpy at times, so keep that in mind if you have small humans at your house all the time or just as visitors. If I was on a dating app, my pick-up line would be "you throw, I catch". Do you like it? Will you give me a try? 

SUBMIT AN APPLICATION HERE: https://www.baltimorecountymd.gov/departments/animalservices/adoption-resources.html

From a volunteer
This is 6 yo Alpine aka Mr Pibbs who came in as a stray. He was confused and very timid at first being in the shelter and didn't present well. However volunteers took him under their wings, and started working with him daily. He's very intelligent and likes challenges like food puzzles and obedience training.
He's a handsome Lab mix just waiting for a forever home, with a big fenced yard for playing ball. He has medium energy and loves activity with his people. He went on a day trip to the park, and was well behaved in the car and walking at the park.

animal.description:
Leopold is still looking for a home or foster home! He is a 2 year old 20 lb Rat Terrier mix. 
New Orleans, LA

Leopold is a sweet boy who was turned into the shelter as a stray. The shelter thinks he was hit by a car but he suffered no real injuries, he just had a wound on his arm that is healed now. 

Leo is a calm, shy boy with lots of love to give. He needs a patient home who can house train him and work on building his confidence. Hes not skittish but you can tell hes been abused in his past. He doesn't seem to know how to play much but he has his own version of playing that tells me he's happy. 

He's a quirky, fun little boy who is sure to find his match soon. He's good with other dogs as long as they aren't too intimidating to him. Hes sensitive, so a large dog who wants to play might scare him, but hes perfectly fine with other dogs who mostly mind their business. He needs a home without cats or kids. He is kennel trained, neutered, and heartworm negative.

animal.description:
Bubba is a male Terrier/Bulldog mix, 6 1/2 mos old as of mid Jan '21 and about 35 lbs so should be about 45 lbs when fully grown. Just a happy go lucky pup ready to learn what life with a family to call his own is all about.
ADOPTION FEES Dogs & Puppies.....$100.00 . This Adoption fee includes: mandatory spay/neuter which will be done before you can take your dog or puppy home with you; basic canine immunizations (DHPP-CPV & Bordatella Intranasal); de-wormings; one-year rabies vaccination if old enough; heartworm test if over five months old; microchip from 24-Pet Watch; certificate for free health examination at your participating veterinarian; and a goodie bag chocked full of information, toys, and more.
The first step to do an adoption is to do our Adoption Application here: https://www.elmorehumane.org/adoption-application-online-form2.html
IMPORTANT - we respond to your emailed applications and queries via email back to you. Please make sure you have either added our email (hselco@bellsouth.net) to your contact list or that you routinely check your SPAM folder for our response just to be safe. If we do not receive a timely response we simply move on to another applicant.
Yes, there are sometimes exceptions to our normal fee for older dogs or special cases. Some of our pets have also been lovingly sponsored by caring people and we will let the approved adopter know about that at the point of adoption. animal.description:
Elodie is a 2 year old Boxer/Hound mix looking for her forever home.  She is about 60 pounds,  Elodie is sweet, playful, and loving. She would love a home with kids ( 8 and up) to play with and people that will walk her and snuggle with her.  She is a little shy of men, but does warm up after a bit. Another dog in the home may help her gain confidence with men . And she would really love another dog in a fenced in yard to romp with. If you are interested in learning more about Elodie, please complete an application and then reach out to Jen.Lu@bigfluffydogs.com

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please apply online, at https://bigfluffydogs.com/adopt/adoption-application/. 

Our main website, www.bigfluffydogs.com has more information about us and the rescue process. 

NOTE TO EMAILERS FROM PETFINDER: WE DO NOT RESPOND TO EMAIL INQUIRIES WITHOUT AN APPLICATION. WE REGRET WE CANNOT RESPOND TO EVERY EMAIL, BUT UNLESS YOU FILL OUT AN APPLICATION, WE DO NOT KNOW YOU EXIST. 

All known information about an individual dog is provided in its listing. We do our best to provide accurate information, but adopters should understand that each home is different and the dog may behave differently in a new home. Dogs are creatures of their environment and you help make the dog what it will be. Homes considering adopting a puppy must be prepared for 1.) Flexible schedules for potty training. Puppies can only hold it for one hour per month of age (i.e. a 4-month-old puppy can only go 4 hours without a potty break). 2.) Crate training until the puppy is at least one year old to prevent chewing on inappropriate things when you can't supervise. 3.) Socialization.  The more positive and varying experiences as a puppy the better, both in and out of your home. 4.) Puppy behavior and life stages are equivalent to a human toddler. It takes at least a full year to have a calmer, well-adjusted dog. Patience is required and when your dog's behavior is a positive experience for you and those around you, your patience will be rewarded ten-fold, for years to come.  Please do not consider adopting a puppy if you have not thoroughly thought through the pros and cons of having one. So many people end up returning them after 3-5 months because they didn't realize the amount of work involved in raising a puppy.  Patience, appropriate toys, socialization, and obedience training are all musts. All are time-consuming and can be expensive. All dogs require supervision with children and obedience training. Adopters that want to have good dogs must be prepared to put the time and effort into training a dog. Any dog requires work and effort, but a well trained, well-socialized dog is more than worth the effort to get them there.

animal.description:
Sweet Abbi, or as we like to call her Miss Abbi Jo, was rescued from a shelter in Cheyenne, WY.  According to the people who brought her to the shelter, she lived her life tied up outside and she was left abandoned at her residence when her owners moved.  

Abbi is a 4 year old Rottweiler (possible Rottweiler mix), weighing about 70 lbs.  Abbi is petite, but strong and loves, loves, loves to snuggle. She likes to jump up on the couch next to you and lay right across your lap, getting as much human contact and love as possible.

Abbi is housebroken, she does fine in a crate if you aren't at home, but she also does fine left unattended in the house while we are away.  She sleeps on a dog bed at night, she rides well in a car and does great at the vet. She gets along well with her very passive male Lab/Golden foster brother.

She is learning her leash manners, she is doing well but sometimes does pull. She is a bit of a work in progress because she gets so excited to go for walks. When excited she can be mouthy and jump up but does not bite. 

Abbi is kind of a spaz when she plays with toys.  She never had them before in her life so it is understandable, and pretty adorable. She can be a bit growly if you try and take a toy away from her, she doesn't want to stop playing!  She has been learning about trading toys for high value treats.

Abbi does have a high prey drive, a home free of cats and small dogs/animals would be best.

Abbi would love to find a forever home with people who love to go on walks, who will give her plenty of toys that she can toss up in the air and run around with and who will allow her to snuggle up to them as much as possible.


If you're interested in meeting Abbi or in learning more about her, please contact Golden Bond Rescue at info@goldenbondrescue.com.

Adoption Fee: $500 + $35 microchip fee
 

* * * * * * * * * *
Evie is being fostered in West Linn, Oregon

PACIFIC NORTHWEST APPLICANTS ONLY: Oregon, Washington, Idaho, Northern California and Southern British Columbia. Please do not inquire if outside these areas.

Golden Bond DOES NOT adopt to families with children under 10. Home ownership and secure 5-foot fencing is required.

See our website, www.goldenbondrescue.com for more information.

Dogs are creatures of their environment and you help make the dog what it will be. Homes considering adopting a puppy must be prepared for 1.) Flexible schedules for potty training. Puppies can only hold it for one hour per month of age (i.e. a 4-month-old puppy can only go 4 hours without a potty break). 2.) Crate training until the puppy is at least one year old to prevent chewing on inappropriate things when you can't supervise. 3.) Socialization.  The more positive and varying experiences as a puppy the better, both in and out of your home. 4.) Puppy behavior and life stages are equivalent to a human toddler. It takes at least a full year to have a calmer, well-adjusted dog. Patience is required and when your dog's behavior is a positive experience for you and those around you, your patience will be rewarded ten-fold, for years to come.  Please do not consider adopting a puppy if you have not thoroughly thought through the pros and cons of having one. So many people end up returning them after 3-5 months because they didn't realize the amount of work involved in raising a puppy.  Patience, appropriate toys, socialization, and obedience training are all musts. All are time-consuming and can be expensive. All dogs require supervision with children and obedience training. Adopters that want to have good dogs must be prepared to put the time and effort into training a dog. Any dog requires work and effort, but a well trained, well-socialized dog is more than worth the effort to get them there.

animal.description:
Jeanette of the Alvin and the Chipmunks litter is a sweet, rambunctious Black Mouth Curr, was born at the end of October and was headed for a life of stardom in the Big Apple. But 2020 struck again, and now she’s living the good life in the Big Easy with another foster puppy who is her best friend and wrestling partner. She idolizes the adult dog she’s living with and gets along great with the two resident cats. 
She was born in late October 2020, she’s UTD on vaccines and is microchipped. She’ll be a large girl when full grown. She’d be great in a home with other dogs and/or children or with someone who is active. 
She loves to play chase and run around, and then nap for a few hours. She sleeps through the night, gated in a room with her foster sister. 
She knows sit really well and we are working on potty training. This little star is hours of entertainment and is looking for a permanent gig with her forever family!

Please note: as with most rescue puppies, we have no way to guarantee this puppy’s breed or size potential. 

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2021 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

animal.description:
Meet Stanley. He is a 95 pound Black and Tan coonhound. He is 7 years old. Stanley does need to lose some weight so he is on a diet. 

Stanley would do best as an only pet. He definitely cannot live with cats, small mammals, or dogs under 30 pounds. Being a hound he has a high prey drive. He also can be protective of his toys with other dogs.

Stanley loves people! He is all about his family. He has been around kids, but would recommend older kids due to his hunting instincts. He has never shown any aggression towards people. 

We are working on some manners with Stanley. He does have a very bad habit of counter surfing which we are trying to break. He pulls on leash, but does well with a no pull harness. He is crated when we are not home. He is not a fan, but will go in with some prodding. At night he sleeps in a dog bed in the bedroom.

Stanley does well in the car. He rides well in the back seat. We do have to help him into the car. 
Stanley is a great dog, but needs the right home. If you would like to meet this dog please call Annie at 815-685-0746.  The adoption fee is $225.

Adoption fee includes:
- microchip
- spay/neuter
- age appropriate vaccinations:  Bordetella, DH(L)PP, rabies
- heartworm preventive & flea/tick preventive 
- deworming

animal.description: This strikingly beautiful girl is Lucy!  We believe her breed to be Rat Terrier (possibly Australian Shepherd mix) born 04/08/2020.  In her previous young life, Lucy had been in a sad situation that led her to come into rescue extremely underweight.  These pictures are deceiving, in that they make her look much bigger than she really is.  Lucy is a very sturdy dog in a small dog body.  Currently she is 16 pounds and will probably, at her ideal adult weight, be about 18 pounds.  With her still being considered a puppy, we would like to find a home for her where there is someone home with her most of the time who will put her on a schedule and work with her.  She would do well with children at least 14 years and up.  We will also require that her new owner will enroll her in training classes.  Lucy is very energetic and is a hard, roughhousing player with the other foster dogs, of all sizes, in her temporary foster home.  She would love another dog in her new home to play with.  She loves to play ball and enjoys a good game of tug of war with the other fosters.  A fenced yard would be a plus!  Her adoption fee includes a crate, training literature, toys, collar, leash and name tag. If interested in Lucy, please call 248.344.0181 (no emails!) and leave a message...if we are not able to answer at that time. If the dog you are inquiring about is still available, your call will be returned. Thanks so much!

animal.description:
Mo came from animal control so we have no history on him, but he is probably 9 years old or older.  They listed him as a Rottweiler mix based but we really don't know what breed he is.  They asked us to take him because he was completely shut down in his run and wouldn't lift his head or even look at anyone.  We didn't want him to die there so we went and picked him up.  We are so glad we did.  

He is a very friendly, calm dog.  He is very shy at first, but once he's comfortable in a new home his personality really starts to shine.  He loves all people and seems to get along with all dogs.  We don't know about cats.  

Mo enjoys hanging out with his family and will lie quietly chewing a bone or a toy.  He loves the company of other dogs, both male and female.  He plays a little, but isn't energetic enough to play much.  He struggles a little with stairs, so he'd do best in a home without stairs or with very few.

Mo is currently going through heartworm treatment and will be finished in mid-February.  He will be ready for adoption at that time.

Mo is housebroken and very well crate trained.  He has been fully vaccinated, neutered and microchipped.  His adoption fee is $250.

animal.description:
Meet Sweetey....

Sweetey is a Papillon mix. Approximate a year and half year old.

We think she recently had a litter of puppies before we got her, but she is very skinny.

Mayte's Rescue saved her from a horrible life on the streets of the Dominican Republic. She has suffered - so she needs lots of love and good food!!

She doesn't trust bigger dogs - she must have had an altercation with on during her previous life on the streets - but with love and patience, we think she could overcome it since she is so young and loving.

She loves to walk and snuggle.

She knows how to stand up for herself, but luckily in her new life she won't have to.

She's a survivor, and it shows in her personality. This girl will need some TLC.

For more info on how to apply to adopt Sweety, please email:

rescue@mayte.com

michael@maytesrescue.com

animal.description:
Princess is an approximately 3 year old pittie who loves to love on humans!

This is what her foster mom has to say:

"Princess is adjusting well. She is definitely nervous but is settling in. We are starting to see her personality. She loves to play with the tennis ball and she loves to cuddle with us on the couch. She had a couple accidents that we think were from nerves, but is otherwise housebroken. She knows sit, stay, paw, and no. Princess seems to have a high prey drive, she wants to chase all the bunnies and squirrels, so we are not sure she would do well with cats.

We are working to get her to walk better on a leash, she is controllable but walks very fast. She sleeps well and waits for us to get up in the morning. She definitely has some separation anxiety, as she follows us everywhere, but she did okay in the crate when we left. She went right in, it just took her a bit to settle (we left our blink camera out to keep an eye on her). 

She loves to run and play fetch, she will do best with a secure, fenced yard. Altogether she is a really good dog! A couple of things to work on but she will make a great companion."

FOLLOW THESE INSTRUCTIONS TO BE CONSIDERED: 

To adopt, complete the application at tarnj.org/adopt

If you have any questions at all, please DO NOT use the PetFinder inquiry form as we do not respond to those. Questions should be sent to info@tarnj.org. 

An application is required before any meets are scheduled so the best way to be considered is to apply ASAP at tarnj.org/adopt.

We are all volunteer-run and do our best to respond to every application. If there is a match with your application, you should hear from us within 2-5 days. If you do not hear from us, please check your Junk folder or email us for an update.

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Cash. I am an approximately 5 year old male staffordshire pit bull terrier mix that weighs around 63 lbs. I am neutered and up to date on vaccinations, microchipped, and heartworm negative. They don't know a lot about my past, but I lived outside my whole life on a run. I had a family before but my little human brother was diagnosed with cancer and I was no longer able to live with them anymore. My foster parents knew my previous family and they couldn't stand to see me go to a shelter, so they brought me to their house to find a new family to love me forever. Since then, I have discovered there is nowhere I'd rather be than in the laps of my foster parents getting cuddles and snoozin the afternoon away! I have also learned many new tricks like sit, place, stay, down, and paw. I love tiny humans and am very gentle with them, but they tell me I'd do best as an only dog as I tend to be somewhat dog selective. Despite this, I could probably pair well with a non-dominant dog with a proper introduction. I will need an adopter who is willing to be patient with me, as when I get nervous or scared sometimes I have accidents inside, but I am a quick learner and always aim to please. Thanks to many unfortunate changes in my environment, I can be a little anxious sometimes and cry because a lot of change can be scary, but with the right family who will work with me and teach me how to be an inside dog, I will relax and settle in quickly. I am crate trained and house trained, aside from my occasional accident when anxious. My ideal family is one that will not give up when I don't understand and that will be patient with me, maybe someone with kids that want someone to play and cuddle with me. I have a few quirks, but I'm a giant goofball who loves to ""tap"" dance when I'm happy and chew on bones. If you look past my breed's bad wrap and give me a chance I'll be the perfect addition to ant home. Don't you want me in your family?

If you are interested in giving Cash a forever home, please visit the link below to fill out an application! http://fureverafterrescue.org/adoption-application.html It is best to submit an application through a computer. We have experienced some problems when applications have been submitted using a mobile device. *When you submit the application, you are not obligated to adopt however it does reserve for you the opportunity to adopt that particular animal. We review them on a first come first served basis. If your application is approved, we will contact you and allow you the opportunity to adopt. If you choose not to adopt, we will contact the next approved applicant. If you have any questions or difficulties, please contact us and we will be glad to help!

Hi, my name Betty Jo. I recently came into VIP Rescue and I am looking for my new home soon! I am very smart and I love to be outside. I a, thought to be a street dog, my rescuers think I have never had an indoor home. Now that I know what this is I love it. I recently learned how to walk on a leash, and I love that too. I prefer to do by business on the leash. I love to explore my fenced backyard.

I am potty trained, I need my new home to offer lots of love and patience. I prefer a home with a fenced yard, as I mentioned I love to be outside. I’m good with other dogs, I’m not picky about age or size. If I had a furry sibling that would probably be good thing I like to play with my foster brother, although he isn’t much interested in me. I am not cat tested, however I do have a prey drive, and love to look for squirrels and birds while I’m on my leash walks. And if given the chance I will chase them.

I am eagerly looking for my perfect forever person or family to call my very own! A meet and greet will be required.

Betty Jo is thought to be approximately 3 years old and weighs 17 lbs. I am most likely a terrier mix. I am spayed, current on my shots, microchipped, and on flea and heartworm prevention. I am heartworm positive. This means I have to take things easy for a while. I also must go see my doctor to get treatments…. so you have to be available to take me to these date sensitive appointments in Palm Harbor. My new family must be in Pinellas, West Pasco or NW Hillsborough. We are accepting applications from experienced pet parents with a fenced yard. Please submit your application to VIPRescue.org. And please share this post to help Betty Jo find her forever home.

animal.description:
Hi there!  My name is Sebastian! I am a Labrador Retriever and I am 7 years old and I weigh 70 pounds!

I was part of a group of dogs that a rescue started helping in a bad part of town. Rescues had come in and picked all the youngsters and left me and an older lady doggie friend all by ourselves on the street. Finally, after a lot of networking, a rescue heard we were still there and came to get us. I hopped right in her car but my friend, well, she had to get fancy and corner in someone's yard! I was SO friendly, I was trying to help our rescuer get my buddy the whole time! Didn't she know a good person when she saw one???

I had called shotgun in the car and was immediately our rescuer's best bud. I kept popping her hand off the shift to stick my head under it so she could pet me better. I'm very considerate that way and still do that whenever I'm sitting next to someone and I think they've forgotten how to pet me. They got me neutered, up to date on shots, current on heartworm/flea prevention and microchipped. Unfortunately, after a long time of being on the street with no one to take care of me, I was heartworm positive but I have already been through treatment and am raring to go....to my new home with YOU, of course!  I would make you proud to be my parent!

I really love all people....little ones, big ones, tall ones and short ones, young ones and old ones..... it doesn't make any difference to me! I would love a home with just about anyone who would show me affection even if they've got kids or grandkids running around. I'm a little bit older boy so I don't need quite as much action as some of those youngsters out there but I still like to go for a walk down the road with my foster mom and I get super excited when I see people! I would probably do best in a home as an ONLY DOG or maybe just with a SUBMISSIVE FEMALE. My foster mom is still working with me all the time to make me the best boy I can be!

I am still located in Houston, Texas but am super excited to find my forever home and get transported to your area! Will you be my family? I promise you won't regret it.  I will be your best friend for a long, long time!  If you would adopt me, my adoption fee is $450 and that covers my flight to Seattle (only availability during COVID-19), my vetting, microchip, travel crate, cost of the flight and a Health Certificate needed in order to travel out of state.  See?  I'm a real bargain!!!  So, if you live anywhere around Seattle or within driving distance, please email doggydarlings12@gmail.com and you will make me a very happy boy!

animal.description:
Samson is a gorgeous fawn-colored boy with a sweet disposition. He's estimated to be around 2 years old and still has quite a bit of that playful puppy in him, but it's definitely manageable as he is well behaved and easily corrected. This big boy (about 65 pounds), will need a home that is somewhat active, has a fenced yard for his playtime and he needs to be an only dog. He also must go to a home that has no cats ... he's not a fan. 

Samson does great on leash and presently walks the neighborhood every day in his foster home. His only issue with walking is he does not care for other dogs, so he barks when he sees one. He is corrected by simply turning in another direction away from the on-coming intruder. After a walk, he's all about snuggling ... in your lap, if you will allow! Well, what dog doesn't think they will fit in your lap?! He loves all people, young and old, big and small and on his walks when kids see him and want to pet, that's just fine with Samson. With all of this said, Samson gets to go to Hound Lounge every week to play and he does just fine there with other dogs, so his barking at other dogs when walking might be a ""being protective of his human"" thing and with some training, this may be something that can be corrected. 

Samson came into our program when he and another dog, possibly Samson's mother, were dumped near PInnacle Mountain State Park, west of Little Rock. Once at the vet's office, it was discovered he had several things going on, mostly parasites, but he did have a light care of the dreaded heartworms. His rescuers took care of all of his vetting (shots, neuter, microchip) and he is now 100% up to date and heartworm free! 

Samson is a polite dog and a calm dog. He is excellent in the house, never bothering a thing inside. Samson's foster mom is quite petite and she handles him beautifully. Samson is also good in the car and great at the vet. He is housetrained and kennel trained too! HIs adoption fee is $150.

If you are interested in adoption, please begin with our adoption application. The link is just below. 

PLEASE MAKE SURE YOUR CITY ALLOWS THIS BREED BEFORE APPLYING. THIS DOG IS PUREBRED PIT AND SOME MUNICIPALITIES DO NOT ALLOW THIS BREED. PLEASE VERIFY THIS BREED IS ALLOWED BEFORE APPLYING.

To make the best possible match for you and the pet, please click below to complete the Adoption Application. 

Once your application has been processed, we'll be in contact. 

We cannot schedule a meet and greet without a completed application. 

If you are viewing this page through PetFinder, Adopt-a-Pet, etc., please go to http://ootwrescue.org/adoption.html to fill out an application or review our Adoption Process.

Needs six foot fence or leash walk only

1 year old Keanu finds himself in need of a new home. He got away one to many times at his home in North Carolina, when tied out on the front porch.  He was hit by a car, but suffered a minor flesh wound that is now healing. 

This good boy does like other dogs and to snuggle. He is getting neutered and will be available soon after.  75 lbs. Black Shepherd. We were told he does need to be fed separate from other dogs, as  he reacted to other dogs walking by his kennel while being fed (not unusual).


If interested in adopting please fill out our no obligation online application at www.puppypawsrescue.org 

Note: Our rescue requires that all adopter's current and prior animals are up-to-date on vaccinations (DHLPP & Rabies)  and preventatives (heartworm and flea and tick), unless there is a medical reason not allowing it. All animals in your household should be spayed or neutered unless medically indicated that they should not be or are currently still too young.

Say hello to Blue! 

She is a 7 year old Pit Bull mix who weights about 50 pounds. Blue recently arrived to our shelter after her owner was no longer able to care for her. Blue is selective with her canine friends, so she would need to be the only dog in the home. If there are children in her forever home, they would need to be ages 10 and up. This senior sweetie is an affectionate pup who can't wait to find her forever home. 

If Blue looks like your new companion, give us a call at 234-212-9843 to schedule an appointment to meet her today!

animal.description: Thor is a bully breed male dog about 2 years old. He absolutely loves people and will hug you and try to get in your lap if you sit with him. He craves attention and really wants an owner and a home, but staff and volunteers are so limited, it's tough to give him more than a few moments of attention per day in a busy shelter setting with so many other pets to tend. Please come meet him and spend some time with him. Thor is desperate for a forever home. He likes to play, but in a shelter setting with a lot of dogs, he is excitable, so we have him in his own fenced area when he goes outside. He may not be the best with other dogs. Thor is a beautiful, muscular dog with ears that stand up. These photos were taken 1/9/20. He came to LCSPCA several months ago as a transfer from county animal control. This wonderful fellow has not gotten adopted yet because his ad fell through the cracks and we just found he was not even on Petfinders. Please call (434) 374-8076 or email lakecountryspca@yahoo.com to adopt. Visit LCSPCA Mon-Sat. from 12-4 om at 11764 Hwy. 15, Clarksville, VA 23927.

animal.description:
Hello!  Thank you for checking out McBugle's listing.  Please read carefully for details on our adoption process:
•First, please note that we are unable to receive correspondence through Petfinder’s system.  Any messages sent through Petfinder or any buttons on this listing will unfortunately not reach us. If you’re interested in adopting please visit www.sanctuaryrescue.com and submit an adoption questionnaire under the forms section.
• Applications for puppies are open for two to three days in order to give ample opportunity to prospective adopters. At the end of this 48-72 hour period we will change the adoption listing to “Applications Closed”. At this point we will begin reviewing all applications received. Next, foster parents will contact approved applicants to set up a meet and greet. This can take up to 1 to 2 weeks.
• Once a dog is officially adopted we will remove its listing from Petfinder. So if this listing is gone, this dog has found its forever family and is no longer available.
• Since Covid lockdown orders, we have seen a massive increase in people interested in adopting dogs (yay!). This means each dog, especially puppies, receive multiple applications in the couple of days we have applications open. There is usually several applicants for one puppy. If it doesn’t work out this time, please understand this is not a personal judgement but likely a result of supply and demand. We encourage you to reapply in the future.

This lucky pup landed in the lap of Sanctuary Rescue with five siblings We are estimating them to be about nine weeks old. We never met mom or dad so breed and size is a pure guess. We estimate they'll be in the 40-50 pound range when full grown. These pups spend their time wrestling with the siblings, lounging around the house, playing tug and just enjoying some good old puppy fun. These pups are well socialized and love everyone they meet. They are young enough to learn about cats.

McBugle's foster says: "McBugle loves to snuggle. She is shy, sweet, and curious about the cats in the house (who are less than interested). She loves to play with her toys. Laesh and potty training are in progress."

MCBugle's adoption fee is $295, which includes age-appropriate vaccinations, spay, and microchip. If you would like to make this gorgeous girl a part of your family, please visit sanctuaryrescue.com and complete an adoption questionnaire under the “Forms” tab.

animal.description:
I'll be your best friend!
I am looking for my forever best friend! My personality is the epitome of what it means to be a heeler. I want to be around my person and alwaystouching them when we are together. I love to play tug, chew bones, and get exercise. If I can cuddle while doing so, even better! Most importantly, I LOVE CARS! I always want to hop in the car or truck.I am afraid of new experiences, but I am brave. As long as I can smell around, I will warm up to the new person, place, or thing. Although I am deaf, I constantly check in and read the social cues given by people and other animals, aswell. I'd do best in a home with children 13 years and older.

General Socialization Notes:

 I have lived with cats and older children. I do fine with some dogs, but will need a slow introduction and very specific boundaries in the house as I tend to guard resources. While outside on a leash, I have only shown positive interest in other dogs. When I am uncomfortable with another dog, I will warn them with a low growl.Typically, I warm up quickly after my warning. I have not had any accidents inside.I am fully potty trained. I love my crate!I am learning to walk on a leash, but I pull and try to play tug with it. I am a bit mouthy and need help to curb that behavior.

Does Stark like other pets?

 I have lived with cats prior to my foster and showed little interest. I show a lot of interest in the cats I live with currentlybecause they react to me.I do betterwith female dogsthat are my size.I have shown extreme resource guarding with the large dogs whom I live with currently. I am working on that. Outside of the house, I only show positive interest in all dogs.

Does Stark like children?

 I have only lived with teenagers prior to my foster home. Outside of the home I have not enjoyed watching kids run around. They make me nervous. I'd do best in a home with children 13 years and older.

Favorite Toys:

 I love rope toys to play tug. I also enjoybones, kongs, and other hard chew toys. I would probably enjoy soft toystoo, but my foster siblings rip soft toys to pieces before I have a chance to play with them.

Ideal Forever Home:

 A home with active people think bicyclists or runners would be wonderful!I have alot of energy.I would love it if you allow me to go on car rides with you daily because I love the car.I need someone with a lot of patience and someone willing totrain with me especially since I'm deaf! I would love a place that likes cuddles and constant interaction. I bond with my person& quickly and would love to give you all my loyalty and companionship!

animal.description:
I may be big, but that doesn't mean I can't be a lap dog!
I am extremely friendly and such a happy girl! I love meeting new people.I love laying in my human'slap and getting all the attention. Being close to my human means a lot to me.Walks are my favorite part of the day and I love running around outside, especiallyin the snow. I'd do best in a home as an only dog. I'm still learning my manners. A home with children 13 years and older would be best too.

General Socialization Notes:

I am great with people. I love getting attention. I get very excited when I see dogs while I'm out on a walk and I might do best in a home as an only dog. I would love to train with my human, so I can learn my manners and bond.

Does Amari like other pets?

 I get extremely excited initially when I'maround other dogs. It is hard to control my excitement.I might be a bit pushy. I'd do best in a home as an only dog. I'm not too sure about cats because I haven't met any.

Does Amari like children?

 I am not too sure. I have not met any children while I've been in my foster home. I might be a little over exuberant being aroundlittle ones, so maybe a home with children 13 years and older would be best for me.

Favorite Toys:

 Ropes and bones are my favorite! I love burying my bones too.

Ideal Forever Home:

 I would love to be ina homewhere Ican take frequent walks, play ina nice backyard. I'd enjoyhumans who cangive me lots of attention. Training will be very important for me. I sometimes do not like being alone, but I am doing okay with that. I'd do best as an only dog and in a homewith children 13 years and older.

animal.description:
Hello hello! I am a big boy named Lil Bit. How cute is that?! I am still pretty young at 19 months of age. What are your expectations in a young dog? If you are expecting me to be loving, easily trainable, and a best friend -- you are right on the money. In addition, if you think I might like water, swimming, and going on adventures with you -- you would win an award for Accuracy! I am all of those things! I like affection, I like people, I love to play with other dogs (though, while playing, I may intimidate small dogs because of my big size), 

I am truly am a great mix of the best parts of being a dog: I love to play and run and chase, and then I also love to sprawl out across my person's lap (taking up half the sofa hahaha). I soak up your love because I am perfectly happy being quiet and content too. I am a big lover. 

I am a happy boy and I love treats so when we meet, it's best to have a pocketful of them ready to share with me. I had a very wonderful previous owner who took great care of me but who recently passed away. In me, you get a Great Dog who is already had a good amount of training and who is the perfect mix of Fun and Cuddle. If I sound like the dog for you, let's meet soon! Love you, Lil Bit

animal.description:
"Sometimes, best friends have four paws." Lada is a happy, friendly, submissive girl who enjoys belly rubs. She will stand and stare at you to get your attention. Lada gets along with other dogs and will play when she wants to. Lada is a low to moderate active Pyr who enjoys sleeping on the chaise.

The Great Pyrenees Rescue Society retrieved Lada, born around November 2016, weighing about 72 lbs, from a Texas animal shelter as a stray. Lada is house trained and has had some basic training (knows to sit and shake). She walks well on a leash, rides nicely in the car, and loads in and out without help. Lada will bark if something isn't normal outside but will quiet down with a simple "uh-uh." She doesn't like cats and stray dogs.

She would do well as an "only dog" in a family with older, considerate kids, and a securely fenced yard to lounge around would keep Lada happy and safe. She would also thrive in a family with a resident canine companion but must be near her size. She is an affectionate, intelligent girl and needs a confident leader in her family that is familiar with Pyr traits and habits. If you are looking for a best friend with four paws, complete an application for Lada.

All dogs and puppies require VISIBLE fencing

Adoption Fee: $325. (Adoption fee includes spay/neuter, heartworm test, rabies, distemper, parvo and health certificate for travel). Northwest adopters pay the cost of transport to independent transport service ($200). Adoption applications can be found on our website at https://www.greatpyreneesrescuesociety.org/.

ADOPTION, FOSTERING, AND DONATIONS are just some of the ways you can help a rescued dog. We have worked hard to cultivate a large network of volunteers to save this majestic breed. While monetary donations are always much appreciated, you can also help by donating your time as a GPRS foster or volunteer!

animal.description:
Hi there!  My name is Sebastian! I am a Labrador Retriever and I am 7 years old and I weigh 70 pounds!

I was part of a group of dogs that a rescue started helping in a bad part of town. Rescues had come in and picked all the youngsters and left me and an older lady doggie friend all by ourselves on the street. Finally, after a lot of networking, a rescue heard we were still there and came to get us. I hopped right in her car but my friend, well, she had to get fancy and corner in someone's yard! I was SO friendly, I was trying to help our rescuer get my buddy the whole time! Didn't she know a good person when she saw one???

I had called shotgun in the car and was immediately our rescuer's best bud. I kept popping her hand off the shift to stick my head under it so she could pet me better. I'm very considerate that way and still do that whenever I'm sitting next to someone and I think they've forgotten how to pet me. They got me neutered, up to date on shots, current on heartworm/flea prevention and microchipped. Unfortunately, after a long time of being on the street with no one to take care of me, I was heartworm positive but I have already been through treatment and am raring to go....to my new home with YOU, of course!  I would make you proud to be my parent!

I really love all people....little ones, big ones, tall ones and short ones, young ones and old ones..... it doesn't make any difference to me! I would love a home with just about anyone who would show me affection even if they've got kids or grandkids running around. I'm a little bit older boy so I don't need quite as much action as some of those youngsters out there but I still like to go for a walk down the road with my foster mom and I get super excited when I see people! I would probably do best in a home as an only dog or maybe just with a submissive female. My foster mom is still working with me all the time to make me the best boy I can be!

I am still located in Houston, Texas but am super excited to find my forever home and get transported to your area! Will you be my family? I promise you won't regret it.  I will be your best friend for a long, long time!  If you would adopt me, my adoption fee is $450 and that covers my flight to Seattle (only availability during COVID-19), my vetting, microchip, travel crate, cost of the flight and a Health Certificate needed in order to travel out of state.  See?  I'm a real bargain!!!  So, if you live anywhere around Seattle or within driving distance, please email doggydarlings12@gmail.com and you will make me a very happy boy!
animal.name: SEBASTIAN
