animal.description:
Meet Landru:: 2 years old, 140 pounds, Neutered Male Great Dane.

Available for Adoption!

This gorgeous, gentle giant is searching for his forever family! Landru is a big goofy sweetheart who loves to snuggle and love on his people and has a wonderfully loving personality. Landru is friendly with new people, gets along great with the other dogs in his foster home and doesn't bother their dog savvy cat too much (any cats in the home should be used to living with dogs). Landru is a very affectionate boy who has great in home manners, is house broken, walks well on the leash and does well in the crate if needed. 

We will be looking for a home for Landru who has experience with Great Danes and/or Giant Breed dogs (i.e. dog breeds over 100 pounds at a healthy weight). Landru is the second Great Dane we have rescued from the same household with 6 children plus neighborhood children frequenting the home. Expectatiins of Landru and the other Great Dane (already adopted) were unrealistic and we don't want to put Landru back in a home with young children (12+ is ok but must be experienced and respectful with dogs). We don't want to put him back in a situation that he's uncomfortable with. We will be seeking a calm environment for Landru. 

$250 Adoption Fee.

A $10.00 non-refundable application fee is required to submit your adoption application and will be deducted from your adoption fee if you adopt.

All Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue dogs are spayed/neutered, current on vaccinations, heartworm tested, current on heartworm and flea prevention, and microchipped.

Along with other criteria evaluated in the adoption application, a Fenced Yard is required to adopt. 

Please see our Fenced Yard Requirements tab on our website for more information, here:
https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/fenced-yard-requirements/

Our adoption area, unless otherwise specified in their bio, is within a two hour radius of Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue for adult dogs, and within a one hour radius for puppies. 

Please see our Adoption Radius tab on our website for more info, here:
https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/adoption-radius/

TO CHECK AVAILABILITY of any of our adoptable animals, please go to our available pets tab, here: https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/available-pets-for-adoption/

All pets listed here are updated regularly to reflect their availability.

ADOPTION APPLICATION INSTRUCTIONS FOR PEPPERMINT PIG ANIMAL RESCUE:

Before completing the application, please read our ADOPTION PROCESS tab on our website, here: 
https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/how-our-adoptions-work/

To complete our easy online adoption application, please visit our website at PeppermintPigAnimalRescue.org.

All adoption information and applications can be found under the ADOPTION CENTER tab.

Adoption events are held every Saturday in our thrift store from 1:00pm to 4:00pm. Please complete your adoption application in advance so our volunteers have time to screen and contact potential adopters.

IMPORTANT: All applications are reviewed in the order they are received and qualifications are based on best fit for each individual pet. A volunteer will contact you if you are selected for a meet with adoptable pet. Final approval is always made in person.

Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue is a no-kill rescue. Please consider sponsoring a pet or donating to our cause. Click the DONATE tab on our website to learn more about how you can help. THANK YOU !

animal.description:
*****************************************************************
PLEASE READ THOROUGHLY BEFORE INQUIRING
*****************************************************************

--ABOUT CLIFFORD--
Clifford is as intelligent and active as he is gorgeous! This giant German chocolate boy was found roaming a park with other pups and eventually someone realized he had no human with him. He was picked up and when no one came forward to claim him, he came to Buddy Dog to find his furever home! There's no mistaking the shepherd in this boy; he walks, talks, and thinks just like one. He needs a family who can keep up with him. He's a fast thinker and is easily stressed if not properly entertained. While he has not yet learned his manners, he is a friendly boy who greets everyone by jumping up to sniff their face, and he is big enough to reach! His misbehaviors, like jumping and play biting, worsen when stressed. Plenty of exercise, training, and playtime is needed to keep this boy happy and on the path to a being a polite pup. He overwhelms most dogs as he likes to "tackle first, greet later" and doesn't understand that not all dogs want to play with him. He would do best as an only pet until he learns boundaries and will take "no" for an answer.

Key Notes:
-2-year old neutered male.
-German shepherd dog and husky/malamute mix.
-74 pounds and underweight.
-Brought to animal control when found as a local stray.
-Experience with dogs needed; experience with active and intelligent breeds recommended.
-No apartment style homes, small homes, or city living. A large fenced-in yard is ideal.
-Needs and adult only (18+) home.
-Should not live with other animals; could eventually live with another dog after he's had training to learn manners and boundaries.
-No more than 6 hours alone a day; will need a potty and play break.
-Basic obedience training required; would thrive with more advanced training.
-High energy; needs lots of mental and physical stimulation daily.
-Almost housebroken.
-Very strong on leash; still strong but better with a no-pull harness; best on a head collar but still training.
-Jumps up and playfully chews on people.
-Food motivated; knows "sit" and "paw".
-Enjoys playtime with sturdy dogs closer to his size who don't also do not have boundaries.

--THE ADOPTION PROCESS--
If you are interested in adopting this animal, please submit an online application. Applications will be reviewed as received. If in our opinion a pet is a good candidate for you, an adoption counselor will contact you to schedule a zoom chat. If you do not hear from us it simply means either the animal has been adopted or we have not received the right pet for you. The application process is at no charge to you and only needs to be completed once as all applications will be kept on file.

Online applications can be found here: www.buddydoghs.com/forms

Check out our FAQ for answers to most questions here: www.buddydoghs.com/faq

Adopters must be at least 21 years of age and a Massachusetts resident.

animal.description:
Suki is a big boy. He is about 90 lbs. He is so cute and has such a sweet goofy face . He’s mostly a mush although he does have some collar reactivity if someone were to grab him forcefully. He is a pretty good listener and he knows how to sit and wait. He does jump up sometimes which this command is a work in progress. He’s a big brute and a teddy bear too. He loves to cuddle , thinks he’s a lap dog , loves to give you a hug “slurp” in the face occasionally. When your dad and if you cry , he wants to be right on you and kissing your face. He gets very concerned. We have had Suki for 2 years . He came to us with a broken leg . He was rescued by animal control and taken from his previous  owners for neglect . His leg healed perfectly but we as a rescue made a mistake on handling him in the very beginning. Being he wasn’t a behavior dog , and was just medical , one of our rescue partners grabbed his collar to get him into his crate,  and he freaked out and snapped at her face. Being that she has a of short stature he bit her top lip and nose and she had to have many sutures. We have now had him over 2 years and never had there been an incident again. He has never bitten anyone. Our friends come over and he jumps up and gives kisses. We made a mistake in the way we handled him when we first got him , but he has shown us over and over that this is not who he is. He was scared and hurting with his broken leg and reacted,  but he has never had any issue again. We know this may dissuade you from adopting and that’s ok. We are a full disclosure Rescue. We want Suki to be in a home that’s perfect for him. We think Suki would even be great with kids but we can’t adopt him to a home unless children are grown. My 9 year old niece lived with us a while and he was great to her, but that’s our rules, an adult home. If you’re young and newly married and starting a family ,a different dog might suit you better. 
If your the perfect person for Suki you will understand the things I am saying and be mesmerized by his adorable “Scooby Doo” face and googly eyes. He’s such a happy boy and so deserving of a wonderful family who can pay more time and attention to this doll! He is great with other dogs. He does get nervous and uptight sometimes but we have a whole pack of huskies and they are overwhelming sometimes. 
If you may be interested in Suki and you meet the qualifications, you can go to Www. LunaSiberianRescue.Dog and fill out the online application.

animal.description:
STILL LOOKING FOR A NEW HOME!
Meet LILY!
Lily is a beautiful 8 yr old, Treeing Walker Coonhound in need of a new home to spoiler her rotten. She is a sensitive little 60 lb girl who loves to be cuddled and her hugs from her humans. She may be 8 but she is still full of life! 
-Very playful with tons of zoomie energy she loves to play fetch. Her favorite outside toy is her so car ball which she will toss around herself and play chase w herself. She takes daily runs with her current parents. 
NEEDS A FENCED YARD
-Knows several basic commands: sit, stay, come. She walks great on leash and loves to explore.
-Sleeps on a big dog bed and does not get on the furniture. She loves her chew bones. She is so smart she has to have things to occupy her mind and chewing bones or her kong toys is her favorite hobby. She also loves car rides. 
-Good with other dogs and loves to play with them. She is a hunting breed  but NOT a hunting dogs. She loves to chase squirrels and other wildlife but when she gets to them she doesn’t know what to do then. With her gentle, sweet nature, there is a possibility that she could live w a cat with proper introduction and time. 
-Good with kids. Currently lives with a toddler and has been around kids but her tail wacks them in the face and her energy knocks them down. This is sadly why her family needs to find her a new home. 
Fully vetted, spayed and microchipped, Lily’s adoption fee is $125.  Approved home get a two week trial prior to adoption 
Apply at https://forgottenpaws.com/adoptionForm.html
Located in the Atlanta Georgia area

animal.description:
Ralph was returned today because he is territorial. Ralph loved the dog he lived with and he did well at the dog park. He is very protective of his home and when on a leash protective of his family with other dogs. This is something that can be fixed with appropriate training. Training sessions with an appropriate trainer will come with Ralph. Ralph is great with people but does not care for cats. Ralph is 2 years old. When Ralph first came to us he was vomiting quite a bit.  We took him to the vet where they discovered that Ralph swallowed a string that got wrapped around the back of his tongue and went down into his stomach and started to grow into the stomach lining. He went through surgery 
to have that removed.

The dog adoption application is located here:
https://form.jotform.com/31997643682166

This dog is at the Granite City Animal Control in Madison County, Illinois. 



Our Adoption Process: 
*You must complete an adoption application before meeting an animal.
*We do all checks on references and vet checks.  
*Please let your references know we will be calling. 
*Once approved, you can set up an appointment to meet any of the animals at the Granite City Animal Control, or the ones in foster homes. 
*There will be a meet and greet and then a home visit.
*After that you will sign an adoption contract and pay the adoption fee.  

$85 for Rabbits / $80 for Cats / $100 Kittens / $150 for Dogs / $200 for Puppies Six Months & Under

The dog adoption application is located here:
https://form.jotform.com/31997643682166

All our animals are completely vetted with the required vaccinations, microchipped and spayed/neutered before leaving the rescue. 
Including: 
Cats will have FIV/FeLV testing
Dogs will have Heartworm testing
Rabbits will have a wellness check 

______________________________________________________________


Many times we also get feral cats or semi-friendly cats (can be petted but doesn't like to be held) needing barn homes. You will need to provide shelter and food. There are not any adoption fees for barn cats (donations are accepted) but you will still need to fill out the cat adoption form. Just list the number of barn cats you are wanting.  

______________________________________________________________

We are a small foster based rescue but some of our animals are residing at the Granite City Animal Control in Madison County, Illinois until they can be adopted, fostered or pulled by another rescue. 

Pound Pets Inc Rescue can always use more fosters.
If you are interested in fostering, the foster application is located here:

https://form.jotform.com/50784968756173

______________________________________________________________

Pound Pets volunteers cleans the animal control building, we are the caregivers for the animals brought in. Once they come through the door, they become our responsibility. We photograph all animals and post to the Pound Pets Facebook page. We provide them clean kennels, beds, blankets, toys, treats, outside play time, walks and human interaction. We try to comfort the scared, keep the high-energy ones exercised and provide plenty of love and affection to make their time at animal control as less stressful as possible. 

Sometimes they get reclaimed by their families and sometimes they don't. If they don't it is our responsibility to find the adopters, fosters or rescues to save them from euthanasia. 

We get in sick and injured animals as well. They do not sit in their kennels or cages needing veterinary care. Once we see the need for care they are taken to the vet. Sometimes the illness or injury is minor and the city will cover the bill, Other times when it's not, we do. We do all of this on our own dime. We buy the food, the beds, the blankets, the toys, and all the other things that go into care for the animals. Sometimes things are donated and that is wonderful!! We pay the medical bills that the city doesn't. As with most animal controls, there is a limit on what they will do or cover. At Pound Pets, there is no limit. Broken Bones, Surgery, Parvo, Heartworm, etc., if the animal has a chance the animal is given that chance. This is not a shelter but an animal control. 

Pound Pets Inc Rescue can always use more volunteers.
If you are interested in volunteering, the volunteer application is located here:

https://form.jotform.com/40307066949156

______________________________________________________________

We are always looking for licensed rescues to pull cats (including FIV+ cats) and dogs from the Granite City Animal Control in Madison County, Illinois. It's a very small animal control and strays keep coming in.  There are no fees for a rescue to pull. If you can help us, please email the volunteers at poundpetsinc@gmail.com 

______________________________________________________________

Pound Pets Inc Animal Control Facebook Page:
https://www.facebook.com/poundpetsincorporated/

Pound Pets Inc Rescue Facebook Page:
https://www.facebook.com/poundpetsincrescue/

animal.description:
Adoption fee on this dog is $300.

Kyda is a 7 year old long haired female. She was an owner surrender who spent all her life in a backyard with three other German Shepherds. As a result, she had no knowledge of indoors or walks outside her yard. She has been picking up the indoor life quite well. She learned the stairs within a few days, and with only one accident, she now appears to be housebroken, with the use of a dog door. She is also learning how to go on walks and she walks calmly next to her human. She will go into a crate, but it is not her favorite thing, however, she does get crated when the family is out and she has been fine. Kyda sleeps in the bedroom with her foster parents.

Kyda is very uncertain of new humans initially, men more than women. She shies away from big arm/hand movements, but when she gets to know you, she is very affectionate. Kyda is a very sweet girl and takes instruction quite well.  She will be an easy dog to train. She shares the foster home with another German Shepherd alum of GCGSR and does well with her.

Kyda is currently overweight and is on a weight reduction regime. This includes daily walks and two smaller meals a day. Although she is large, she is a slow, picky eater.  

Cats & small critters unknown.

This dog is a Level 2. Please be sure you understand what a dog of this Level requires. Go to our home page for an explanation of the Dog Rating Levels.

For more information and to see when this dog will be attending an Adoption Day, please see our Dogs page on our main website at www.gcgsr.org. 

We operate within a reasonable driving distance from the Greater Sacramento area, the 	Central Valley down to Merced, and Lake Tahoe. A reasonable driving distance is determined by where one of our volunteers is willing to drive within our areas of service. That means we don't adopt out of our area, to Southern California, or Out of State. 


Thank you for visiting!

Meet Lenny!

Lenny (formally known as Cliff) is a beautiful 2-3 year old Pointer. We rescued Lenny from a shelter when he came there with a limp forearm caused by a past gunshot wound and metal fragments still imbedded in his arm as a result. Who could shoot a 2 year old pup?!?! 

Lenny is an easy-going, docile and smart boy. He LOVES people (velcro dog!), loves to cuddle, loves to please and loves calm interaction! A quiet home with older kids may be best since he seems to thrive best in a calm environment. 
You can tell he is a bit shy from what has happened to him, but he is also curious, very sweet and very smart- is even learning new commands!

If you are interested in adopting Cliff, please apply at www.twotailzrescue.org!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.If interested in adopting an available dog read about our Adoption Process and then complete an Adoption Application. Both can be found under the Adopt menu item on the website. A veterinarian evaluates all dogs taken in by Mo-Kan Border Collie Rescue . All required shots are administered; checked for intestinal parasites; heart worms and they are spayed/neutered.

Dogs on the Sponsorship page may or may not be available for adoption yet, but can be Sponsored. Read more under the We Need You menu item on the website.

Courtesy Listings have not been evaluated by MoKanBCR. Please refer to the contact info in the bio.
Hope is an approximately 5 year old border collie or Australian shepherd mix as best as we can tell! Hope came to us extremely under socialized and terrified of people. Her initial reaction was to bolt if possible and flatten herself to the ground or floor if she had nowhere to run. Hope also came into rescue very pregnant and raised five adorable puppies in her foster home.

Hope has come a long way since arriving in rescue. She has progressed from needing to be taken out on a long line and harness in a fenced yard to being able to go in and out with the other dogs without issue. She enjoys being around her foster family and will often follow them from room to room during the day but she is not yet to the point of enjoying a lot of petting or cuddles. She will let us walk up to her in the house or yard (usually) and pet her or put a leash on her but she does not really come up to us and seek attention. She is getting less picky about treats and has taken a definite interest in "snack time" in her foster home. She really enjoys playing with her foster brothers but also doesn't mind living with dogs who don't want to play. She enjoys rawhide strips and nylabones but does not yet play with toys. She likes dogs beds and would be happy to hang out on the couch if we let her! Hope is good with cats as well as other animals.

Hope walks quietly on a leash but but does still get startled and may balk or spook at times. She is housebroken and crate trained. She is getting better about being led by the collar and nail trims. Things like being picked up or bathing or being restrained can still cause her to panic some but I expect her to continue to make progress.

Hope is about 36 lbs but short and stocky. Radiographically, Hope has significant hip dysplasia. While she currently has no clinical signs she could benefit from joint supplements or joint diets and may need additional medication or therapy in the future. Maintaining a lean weight will be important for her.

Hope requires a secure, standard above ground fence. She should still be considered a flight risk, especially in a new environment. Her new family will need to leash walk her even in the fenced yard until she reliably can be caught or defaults to returning to the house when startled or is done being outside. She is a low energy dog who has potential to be a nice companion or walking partner. Young children are not recommended at this time as they could be scary to her.

Hope is being fostered in the Ozark, Mo area.Click here to watch a video of Hope. 2/2/21 11:17 AM

animal.description:
Breezy is a spayed female pit bull terrier/Labrador retriever mix born on 3-10-2017. She is a medium sized dog weighing approximately 50 pounds. Breezy is a low to medium energy girl who enjoys a stroll around the block and a ride in the car with her friends. She has good manners and is just plain fun. With people, she is a submissive girl, who does best with gentle training and correction. She always wants to please!

Breezy has a goofy smile when she is happy. She is a great pet for the right someone, but she is not your fist dog. She needs a loving owner experienced with her breed.

Breezy arrived at Lee Shore with 8 tiny puppies and has done a good job of raising them. Now it is her turn to find that special home. Could it be yours?

She has been friendly towards her foster family and people she has met. Breezy can get along well with other dogs, and enjoys playing. However she is selective and also needs a slow warm-up to new dogs. Her play style is enthusiastic, so her playmate needs to be another strong dog. She should not be around small dogs or cats. She would not mind being the center of attention in a single dog home either!

Breezy can be protective of her people and of herself if there are strange dogs. Her desired home has loving people who will let her be the couch potato of her dreams, has a covered outdoor kennel run, and people who will keep her on a leash, in the house or out for air in a covered run.

Breezy is house trained, crate trained, and leash trained. She has knows basic obedience training. Breezy is spayed and up to date on vaccinations, deworming, and flea/tick meds. Breezy was heart worm positive and has had treatment. The adoption fee for Breezy is $250.

To adopt this loving girl, please go to
https://www.leeshorerescue.com/apply.html
and fill out an application today!

animal.description:
Age:5
Weight: 125
Location: New Britain, CT
Nicknames: Maximus, Lil' Bit, Bubba
Good with other dogs?: Dog selective.
In his previous home, Max lived with three other dogs who were a but smaller than him. I mean, how couldn't they be? Max used to weigh 144.6 pounds! They ate together and played hard together as Max was described as being the most submissive of the four. He came to us with lots of scabs and scrapes which have since healed up. He is happy to see other dogs on walks and wants to play. We are working on introducing him to his foster pack this week.
Good with cats? other: He is interested but isn't quick enough to catch our cat.
Good with children? unknown, will not be adopted to a home with kids under 10
Activity Preference: Needs a couple walks a day.
IQ: Smart
Max's favorite things: Max loves his stuffed toys. He definitely uses them to self-sooth. They last awhile until they die a very fluffy death. He likes a walk around the neighborhood and always needs to say hi to folks, so be ready to meet some new neighbors. He is highly motivated by treats due to his extreme and necessary diet.

Max likes neck scratches and belly rubs and body hugs. But he does not like kisses on his nose at all. It makes him nervous. You can kiss the top of his head if you must.

He also likes to play ball. He loves a tennis ball which was his reward for hitting his first weight loss goal!
Max is good at: meeting people, behaving in the house, going for car rides, making me feel safe, walking on a leash, playing, following commands, other: Taking treats gently
Ideal home: someone at home most of the day, other: Someone who understands dog body language
Training Needs: socialization with dogs
Health issues: Max came to us in an extremely obese state. We are working very hard to get him to a healthy weight and Max is making great progress. Due to his natural size (he should probably be anywhere from 95-115lbs) it is important that his forever home recognize that he stay trim for his overall health. His energy and happiness have increased dramatically now that he is more than 15 pounds lighter in his first month with us.

Meet Max

I'm sure you're familiar with Grumpy Cat. And it could be that Max is related. But don't let his resting frowny face fool you. Max smiles all the time now. Except when I'm trying to get cute photos of him ;)

Max had a really tough start. And we mean really. He was found tied to a poll covered in blood at a young age. A very nice woman took him in and worked with him to get him to trust people again. Max lived with three other dogs who were described as fairly dominant. Max was apparently the submissive one of the group. They were provided with food all the time and we think Max ate his feelings.

Max came to us severely overweight. His long-term foster mom had to move and made the tough choice to give Max a chance at a better home where he could get more attention than her schedule would allow. Tipping the scales at more than 144 pounds, we had to get him to a healthy weight pronto. Max had a tough transition into our house, doing a lot of crying for his lost life. We have never experienced that kind of sadness from a foster and it was heartbreaking to watch. But having been with us for a month now, he is much happier and loves attention and playtime.

Max is perfectly house trained. He will do his business on walks or in the back yard. And he is a pretty easy walker. He takes his harness like a champ and learned the route very quickly. He will let you know if he wants a long or short walk.

Max lets us know when Amazon is here to make a delivery but other than that, he only barks when he really needs to go outside or when one of his toy is stuck. He is completely non-destructive and has not been crated due to his size and initial anxiety. He has his own open space in our home and has been a gentleman. Max joins us downstairs during our Peloton rides. I think he wonders why we are doing all that work, but he keeps us safe while we get our sweat on.

Max loves to have someone by his side. It is when he relaxes the most. However, he is still wary at times, giving me the side eye. He does not like to be kissed on the face therefore, small kids are probably not a good fit for Max. He takes kisses on his head and lets us hug his around his body. He likes neck scratches and will lean into them. When he is comfortable with you, you'll know because he will finally give you his belly. And that is huge and so rewarding. He loves playing with his toys and showing them to you; that is when you will get the biggest smile. Max knows how to sit and shake with both paws. I'm sure he can learn even more tricks. He also likes a car ride.

Max is at the point now where we can tell he wants to be integrated with our group. We have six personal dogs who are all seniors and super seniors. We will be working on introducing him this week to see how it goes with dogs of different sizes.

Anyone interested in Max will get a very easy going dog once he settles into your home. It is important to give him time to adjust. This could take two full weeks or more. But given our experience, it is quite possible that he won't fully blossom until then. He is completely worth it!

PLEASE READ: Adopters will not be considered without completing an application. Please visit www.AmericanBulldogRescue.org to apply! Remember - Adoption is always the best option! If you can't help by adopting a homeless pet, please consider making a tax-deductible donation to American Bulldog Rescue, 4 Terry Drive, Suite 1D Newtown, PA 18940 or paypal AmericanBulldogRescue@verizon.net. We cannot place dogs in homes with children under 10 unless that dog has lived with kids or is in a foster home with kids. Thank you.
To be considered for adoption, you must apply using our free, online application. Our dogs are fostered in our volunteers' homes, not in a central shelter/location. Only approved applicants are put into contact with the foster family to setup a meeting with the foster dog. Visit our Adoption Policies web page for more information and a link to our application: http://americanbulldogrescue.org/adoption-policies/.

animal.description:
Hi, I'm Macei!



When I first came here, I was very shy and being the dog in the back of the kennel, you often get overlooked. Because of the patience, kindness, and introductions to great friends-- each day I have come forward to meet people more and more!



Each morning, I excitedly greet the staff, and every potential adopter who walks throughout the day makes me ecstatic and I have to definitely say hello! I walk very well on a leash, especially when I know it is because I am headed to Rescue Recess playgroups with my friends, humans and doggo's alike! One of my playgroup handlers says "I am a super sweet, cuddly, gentle lady looking for some love" and if you came to meet me, you would see how true that is! I LOVE treats, they are the way to my heart and "[She] would be the perfect friend to cuddle up with."



You should come meet me and experience my wonderful personality for yourself. You would not want to leave the feeling of love and happiness that I give you behind!

animal.description:
Rocky is a bright, bubbly, brindle boy that is about 3 years old and is so ready to leap into your arms and be your best friend forever! Rocky was turned in by his family along with another dog because they were moving and couldn't take them along. Although Rocky is ok with the other dog, he is very dominant with dogs and it would be best if he were an only pet. He sure loves people though! Rocky is your buddy the minute you meet him. He's all smiles and butt wiggles, and he sits right down expectantly, hoping for a treat, a toy, or all of your attention. He's full of energy and goes from sitting to leaping in the air in a second. He needs a home with no small kids, simply because he'll inadvertently knock them over. He would love a home with a fenced yard that he could get his jumpies out in. He'll keep you active and keep you laughing too if you give him a chance! File#29930 12/30/20 Call 609-693-1900 or email: office@ahsppz.org to meet Rocky.

If interested please visit our Forked River Shelter. We are open Mon. - Fri. from 12:00 P. M. - 6:00 P. M.; and Sat. & Sun. 12:00 P. M. - 5:00 P. M. for directions call 609-693-1900. There is an adoption donation required. The society cannot accept personal checks but we do accept Visa, MC, AE, Discover and cash. As part of our adoption process, we must have proof of residency. Homeowners must show proof of ownership; landlord approval is required for renters before an adoption can be approved.And as always we thank you for your kindness in opening your heart & home to a Society orphan.

animal.description:
*PLEASE NOTE:  We do not adopt out on a first-come/first-serve basis.  Applications are accepted for a dog and then a home check is scheduled.  If there are multiple applications for a dog, after all  home checks are done,  the dog is adopted out to the home that is the best fit for that dog.
***** All breeds listed are a best guess or based on information from our rescue partners and are not guaranteed*****
 
 ******Chicagoland Dog Rescue reserves the right to restrict adoption of a dog to potential adopters who live within a fifty (50) mile radius of Schaumburg, IL *****


Hi! My name is Cheyenne and I am anywhere from 1-2 years old but no one really knows for sure my exact age! When I first came to my foster family, I was a VERY skinny, shy pup and wasn't really sure how to act like a dog. After a few weeks, I have come out of my shell a little and showing everyone what a SWEET girl I really am! I get along well with my two foster fur siblings and they are teaching me how to be a dog. I have met cats at the shelter in Alabama and ignored them all but if I lived with one,  I really don’t know if I would want to hang with it or chase it?!? But, I am very calm and good with kids! I feel safe in my crate, but don't like to go in there with the gate closed and will sometimes cry at night. I REALLY love to snuggle and my favorite part of the day is meal time! I sometimes have had some accidents in the house because I don't like going outside in the cold, but I'm working on it!  I am looking for a home with other calm canine buddies, kids, and grown-up people that will understand that the beginning of my life was pretty hard and I will need time to build up my confidence and trust in the outside world.  But I promise to give you lots of love and companionship and all the snuggles you want!  If you would like to meet me, please fill out a pre-adoption application and a CDR volunteer will get back to you just as quick as they can!
Tail wags and snuggles-Cheyenne

**The ADOPTION FEE for this pet is $400-450.00,  which includes getting the puppy/dog up to date on rabies, distemper and bordetella vaccines, fecal test and deworming if necessary, heartworm test, spay or neuter (not including pre-surgical bloodwork) and a microchip. Free access to our weekly training classes is also included for the life of the dog, something no other rescue in the area offers.***

He was adopted out as a puppy but found himself coming back to rescue after his family struggled to work through some of his quirks. *Did I lose you already?* What are Mac's quirks you say? He seems to be afraid of men, at his previous house the man wasn't always home so working with him to adjust to "men are okay" didn't happen and it became to much. She will bark to alert but knows not to dig or chew. She’s still a pup at heart, so she is not entirely trustworthy with free roam yet. animal.description: Hi my name is Lit Bit and I am about five years old. I was a stray on the streets in town and brought here to the shelter to wait for my new loving home. I am kinda shy until I get to know you but I am a pretty good dog and I get along with other dogs and this a a plus if you already have dogs in your home. I am heartworm positive and will get treatment here at the shelter but you can still adopt me now and decide how treatment will be for me. Sometimes when heartworm positive dogs are treated they stay here until  all treatment is finished and sometimes they get to go with their new family and then brought back to shelter on days treatment is given. The shelter will decide this for me and I am okay with that. My adoption fee is $100.00 and this includes my neutering, worming, shots, and micro chipping. I maybe an older fellow but I am a great guy who is needing a loving family to take care of me and I will be their bestest dog.  Oh, almost forgot.... The shelter is closed for a time so just call, email, or use this site to contact the shelter to get an application to be able to see me and adopt me. You will be given a date and time to come to the shelter when approved and then the wheels are put in motion for me to find a new family. Remember I am Lil Bit....

Jenny is a 2 month old lab mix that will be arriving to us from our rescue partner shelter in Louisiana.  She weighs approximately 10 lbs.  She will be arriving to us with her siblings Blair and Chuck on January 30th.

Jenny is pretty independent and easy going.  She is ready to either play or chill out with people.  She just follows along with whatever everyone else is doing.  She is indifferent to cuddling.  

Adoption fees cover age specific vaccinations, spay/neuter, microchip, heartworm/lyme/ehrlichia test, worming and transport fees. 

Adoption fees: 
Through 6 months of age $450; 
7 months to through 5 years $400; 
6 years and under 9 years $325: bonded pairs are $500; 
9 years and older $250: bonded pairs are $300 

FOR PUPPIES: PLEASE READ!!
Homes considering Puppies must be prepared for:
Flexible Schedules for Potty Training. Puppies can only hold urine for one hour per month of age. Crate Training for the next 10 months to keep them safe from chewing on everything in your home. Supervision with Children and Obedience training. 
Socialization; both with new people, children and other dogs outside of the home.
Homes that want a well behaved dog, must be prepared to put the time, effort and costs associated to train a puppy. Well behaved dogs are not born, they are trained!  Please do not apply for a puppy if you cannot or do not have the time for a puppy.

Almost Home Rescue of New England is a 501 c 3 non-profit rescue; rescuing dogs since 2005. All Adoption applications are completed on line at www.almosthomerescue.net 

This dog is available unless it is marked as Pending, meaning Pending Adoption. This dog is in foster care locally, ONLY if Maine or New Hampshire is listed next to the dogs name; otherwise, the dog is still waiting with our partner rescue for an adoption or foster home in New England. 

PLEASE NOTE - We will check your veterinary reference, to ensure that current and prior dogs have a history of being kept up to date on rabies and distemper, have had annual heartworm tests, and are on heartworm preventative at least 6 months of the year. Current pets must by spayed/neutered. 

Imported dogs are transported on a USDA approved transport with a Health Certificate. All imported dogs are quarantined 14 days prior to getting on transport.

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Garrett! 

I may seem a bit shy at first but don’t let that fool you. Once I get to know you, I am a sweet lovable boy! I love going on walks, and swimming, but my favorite activity is being a lapdog and hanging out with my people. I do not do well with small animals probably because of my sporting ancestors, but I love children of any age and have lived with kids ages 7-19 with my brother Wolf! I’m not quite housetrained yet, because I love being outdoors!

I am smart and I pick up things quickly; I even know how to sit when asked! I am also food driven; I love milk bones and pretty much anything else! I don’t dig and I always stay in my yard. My favorite kind of toys are stuffed animals and sticks! I am a content dog, happy to play and relax whenever. I am very low maintenance, super excited to hang out with people and I am well behaved! If you are looking for a wonderful, fun-loving and easygoing canine companion, I am the one for you!

If you feel your home might be the right place for such a great dog - the place to start is with the adoption application found at www.dfwrescueme.org/adopt. Once submitted, the foster will contact you promptly to tell you more and to arrange a time to meet!

The adoption fee for all of our dogs is $250.00, which includes their vaccinations and spay/neuter.

Garrett is participating in the DFW Rescue Me Guest Dog Program, so ongoing care and custody are provided by their foster, not by DFWRM.

animal.description:
Introducing this radiantly wonderful German Shepherd  angel named Elena! She was found in a physical state of actual skin and bones- in advanced starvation, in a busy intersection navigating city streets trying to survive. Thankfully, after what was surely a long time on the streets, a wonderful person welcomed her into their car to try to save her life. They could tell she was in poor shape and brought her to the vets. Fortunately their vets office immediately fell in love with her and wanted to ensure this girl got great care, and wanted to help navigate her towards a better life! 
She had her medical work completed and went to a super nurturing, doting foster home who was happy to welcome this girl into their home and feed her lots of delicious food and bring this girl back to life!
She is definitely a senior, but boy is she absolutely amazing! She is smart as a whip and her foster parents said she can learn just about anything in practically seconds! She knows sir, stay, paw, and has beautiful house manners. She is so eager to please and so sharp. She is confident, strong, silly, a little sassy, and 500% lovable. Anyone with a soft spot for shepherds will be head over heels in love with this girl! She will have conversations with you and is so super loyal and eager to connect! She has a moderate energy level and loves to play! She prefers the companionship of male dogs, though has been good with the ladies also! As a shepherd, she just has a stronger personality with pups- but she loves them. She would love a brother her size but also loves to play with smaller pups too! Her two favorite things to do are to be outside exploring and hiking and taking in nature, or being on the sofa snuggled up with her favorite people resting her head right on their lap!! She is so loyal and affectionate- she really is an amazing old soul. She has gained weight beautifully, and is super great motivated! She is so devoted, she wants to go anywhere she can with you, including lots of car rides and anything fun where she can be by your side! She has done great on and off leash and while she is a senior, she truly is a sharp girl who has so much spunk and wit! She doesn’t show her age a bit. She is in search of a loyal human who will be as devoted to her as she is to them- who will cherish and spoil her through her golden years! 
If you would love to make her dreams come true, and give her the love she has waited most of her lifetime for, please visit our website and submit an application for adoption today! www.greatdivideanimalrescue.org

animal.description:
FAST FACTS:
*1.5 Years old - 35 Pounds
*Playful & Affectionate: Would Love an Active Family
*Dog Friendly
*Children Friendly
*No Apartments/Townhouses
*Fenced (5-Foot Fence) Yard Preferred
*Potty/Crate Trained
*Training Required

BIO:
Wanna go for a walk? My name is Winnebago (Winnie for short), and I am a playful, affectionate little lady who would love an active family to enjoy strolls and hikes with for the rest of my life. I have a medium energy level: I love to be your exercise buddy on long walkies but am also a great work-from-home companion and happily lay next to you while you take care of human business. I am one of the friendliest furballs you will ever meet: I get along with people of all ages (even kiddos) and looove saying hi to everyone we pass while strutting around the neighborhood. I get along with other dogs but my excitement to make new pals can be overwhelming to some pups, so a slow introduction is recommended.

I'm a smartypants, too: I am potty trained and love my crate when the door to it is open. I much prefer to be around my people and can be vocal when crated while you are gone so I would do best in a single-family home without shared walls (no apartments/townhouses/condos for me, please!) I would also love a yard with a tall fence (5-foot minimum) at my forever home so I can run some zoomies to my heart's content. I know a bunch of commands already including sit, come, lay/down, up, and even know my name already. I would thrive with continued training so I can work on my leash skills and focus when outside since I am such a social butterfly and pull to greet potential new friends. I think training will be the first of so many fun adventures we have together! Just imagine it: long, beautiful hikes followed by cozy cuddles on our comfy couch. If that sounds like the dream life to you, please fill out an adoption application so we can live the dream together!

Love,
Winnebago

ADOPTION REQUIREMENTS, NO EXCEPTIONS:
*ADOPTION FEE: $300
*Be at least 21 years of age
*Live in a 50-mile radius of Itasca, within the Illinois border
*Have the knowledge and agreement of all adults living in the household
*Have approval from owner of residence (written in lease)
*Have a valid ID with current address (please provide proof of address if ID address is not up-to-date)
*Be approved as a suitable adoptive home by Fetching Tails Foundation
*Be prepared to make a lifetime commitment

If interested please fill out an application on our website at www.fetchingtailsfoundation.org; please make sure you fill in every required field/question or your submission will not go through. Please note that we take time to learn as much as we can about each dog in our care and our bios are our current observations; we are unable to make any guarantees on the future health or temperament of your adopted dog. Most dogs in our care come with unknown pre-rescue history and as such breed and age estimates are an educated guess.

animal.description: Welcome to Bear country. ha, I like to think this because I will have been here a year 1-28-2021. I had  to come here because my person was allergic to me.  I am about three years old, well  about four after Jan. 28th. I am very handsome. I am picky in who I like and I am a fear biter. I do not need to be around children at all because of my biting habit. I would make a good farm dog where I could do my own thing and nobody would have to touch me. The manager here thinks I would be better with men. I do know I am so tired of this cage. I do get to go outside in one of the fenced in areas and I love that. One day I actually got to walk around the building my cage is in and  I was a different dog. I was nice. I will just have to be honest with you, I do not like things done to me like shots and I have to be muzzled for that. I just want to be and to be left alone. You can talk to me but I will be barking at you at the same time. I sure hope there is someone out in this big world that wants a Bear in the family. Contact the shelter by email. this site, or calling and ask for an application to see me. Just maybe I am  the dog you have been looking for and need for your farm. I am Bear and yes, I am a hard to place dog but there is someone for everyone in this world, just have to keep looking and looking and hoping.

animal.description:
The Basics: Hello! I am Nutmeg! My sister, Sesame June, and I are frequently described as the most “beautiful and perfect pair”! Plus, we are world travelers – I was once a street dog from Azerbaijan which you’d never be able to guess with how well behaved I am! My foster mom says I am the “alerter”, while my sister is the “hunter” when we see squirrels! We absolutely love one another and can often be found snuggling, wrestling, or sneaking a kiss or two.


Heartbreakingly, we found out I have Stage 3 Kidney Disease and a kidney stone that is being treated with a special diet and quarterly blood tests that will need to be kept up for the rest of my life. We are searching for a super loving home that will provide the dedicated care needed while I am here and for my sister, when I am no longer around. Luckily, I am not showing many negative symptoms yet, so we still have plenty of wrestling to do and will not be separated! 

Likes: Staring lovingly into your eyes, barking at squirrels, running around and playing with my sister makes us feel so free!

Dislikes: I can be a little shy and reserved when I first meet you. I am not a fan of quick movements around my head, but I usually am the first of us to warm up to people!

Looking for: A compassionate home dedicated to keeping a close eye on me, my Stage 3 Kidney Disease, my strict diet, and my sister! 

Weight: 22 lbs 

My estimated birth date is: 3/5/2016

I'm in a foster home so if you want to meet me please fill out an adoption application at www.animalaidpdx.org.


Please note: due to our screening preference to view the potential home and interview the prospective guardian, we rarely adopt out of our local Portland metro area.
animal.name: Nutmeg

animal.description:
I am a part of a special needs bonded pair and will NOT be separated. The Basics: Hello, I am Sesame June! My sister, Nutmeg, and I are frequently described as the most “beautiful and perfect pair”! Plus, we are world travelers – I was originally rescued from a dog meat farm in South Korea. My sister may be shorter than me and born in another country, but I love to chase when she alerts me of a squirrel! We absolutely love one another and can often be found snuggling, wrestling, or sneaking a kiss or two. Heartbreakingly, we found out my sister Nutmeg has Stage 3 Kidney Disease, so we need a home that can provide the dedicated care needed while Nutmeg is still here with me! Luckily, she isn’t showing many negative symptoms yet, so we still have plenty of wrestling to do and will not be separated! Likes: Cuddling up with you at night, yummy treats, and greeting you with my favorite toys while standing on my hind legs when you get home! I also love to run and play with my sister! Dislikes: I can be a little shy and reserved when I first meet you. I am not a fan of quick movements around my head, but I gain confidence very quickly… especially when treats are involved! Looking for: A compassionate home dedicated to a bonded pair, and who will spoil me with treats, toys, and a lifetime of adventures! Weight: 26.4 lbs My estimated birth date is: 8/20/2017 I'm in a foster home so if you want to meet me please fill out an adoption application at www.animalaidpdx.org.

Please note: due to our screening preference to view the potential home and interview the prospective guardian, we rarely adopt out of our local Portland metro area.

animal.description: Let me get this over with.... I am Samson and I am about 1 and a half years old. I was brought here to the shelter by animal control because of a complaint. I do not know what a complaint is but I was one. I would probably make a good guard dog for you. I am iffy with other male dogs and children. I might be good with female dogs but I really have not decided for sure about this. I am really, really handsome. I like to run around in  my dog run and bark really loud. My adoption fee is $100.00 and this includes my neutering, shots, worming and micro chipping. Because the shelter is closed to the public because of this awful stuff you can only see me when approved. You can get approved by first contacting the shelter by this site, email, or calling and asking for an application to come see me. After filling out the papers and returning to them to the shelter if approved you will be given a day and time to see me. When you come DO NOT forget your mask. You can visit with me and hopefully fall in love with me and want me for your family. I sure hope I will fit into a family and my new human and I will have a great life I just know. Doing this was not too bad.... I am Samson

Elle is really the full package, she's smart, fun, active and loves to play. She would make a wonderful adventure partner and a great netflix buddy too. If you think you are a great match for Elle, be sure submit an application and she will surely love to show you just how great she is!

animal.description:
In our time with the very handsome 18 month old Ben, we have learned lots of things about him.
18 m Ben is so very ready for a forever family. He is good with most humans he meets and with a proper intro, good with dogs his size. Due to his prey drive, little kids, cars and small dogs are a no. He’s housebroken and knows a few commands but needs training and someone who’s had experience with working dogs.
He enjoys a bit of counter surfing for snacks if given the chance but corrects quickly with a stern OFF.  He is high energy, the kind of high energy you think 45 minutes straight of fetch will burn off and then he’s staring at you and crying to keep going.  He whimpers and vocalizes during play.  Its adorable.  He gets over stimulated and over exuberant and needs to be taken in hand sometimes so a confident owner would benefit him.  We make him sit before we throw his balls so he doesn’t lunge and grab for instance.  We also make him sit for his meals, which he has no problem with any humans being around.
He’s a lover.  A jump up in your face, hug you, and beg you to pet him and throw his ball, l.o.v.e.r.  He can be mouthy when he’s amped up, like most of his breed, but a loud “OW” stops him in his tracks.  With guidance he’s truly a phenomenal dog.  He can be picky about new furry friends but for the most part, if introduced properly, he could easily live a happy life with another dog his size.  We wouldn’t recommend small animals as he has displayed some prey drive and a willingness to act on it with bunnies in our yard and small dogs he’s met.
He is potty trained and will hold it all night or during a work day easily if he doesn’t have access to outside.   He can be a handful but no more than most dogs at 18 months of his breed.   He has a tendency to grab first, ask questions later when it comes to his toys if not kept control of and guided to make the right decisions.  He’s great in a car and loves to go places.  His preference is to ride shotgun in his own way, standing with his head between the seats to see the world around him.
Think you’re Bens dream family?  You can apply to foster or adopt at www.Vegasshepherdrescue.com.  Already approved?  Reach out to us for a meeting.
?

animal.description: Twizzler was left at vet clinic and his family did not return to pick him up. After several weeks the clinic manager, a Southern Skies Adopter, called and asked if we could help a very sweet young lab. Twizzler is a handsome 1 year old, all black with a small white mark on his chest. He weighs 54 pounds but should probably weigh 70 pounds. He was very thin when he arrived at the clinic he was left at, he started gaining weight there and is continuing to eat well. He is currently on puppy food for the extra calories and extra vitamins and nutrients. Twizzler is potty trained. He complains a little at first when he is crated but then calms down. If he barks in the crate it usually means he needs to go to the bathroom. Twizzler is cautious when meeting new people but warms up quickly to them. He is discovering lots of new things, like steps, various outdoor noises and is handling each new thing better as the days go on. He would love another dog to play and has not been tested around cats. He also is so good with young children, no jumping, very gentle. He is young and likes toys but will occasionally grab a shoe or other off limited item, so he needs to be monitored when out of the crate. He does not know any commands but stands still to have his leash put on and is beginning to understand kennel up. I believe he would love the one-on-one experience of training and excel at it. Twizzler is not a jumper, enjoys TV, loves being outside, easy on a leash, very gentle and inquisitive. He will make great hiking walking buddy. He is discovering snuggling; belly rubs and ear scratching are among his favorite things. He likes treats but I do not believe he has ever been handed one so taking one is new, but he is very gentle, no mouthing. He knows when he gets in trouble and does not like it, he is a pleaser and a tail wager! Twizzler would love a fenced in yard. Twizzler is up to date on vaccinations, microchipped but sadly he did test positive for heartworms making him the 31st dog this year SSLR has taken in. His treatment has begun, and Southern Skies will provide the needed treatment that can then go with him. Twizzler also had a common eyelid condition called entropion and he had surgery to correct it. The whole world is just opening up to this sweet, calm, loving boy, would you like to show him how great the world can really be? Please apply and complete our online pre-adoption application if you are interested in Twizzler becoming a part of your family. http://www.southernskiesrescue.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Meet Lilly!

"Hi everyone! My name is Lilly and I am a terrier mix. I’m shy but very lovable once I feel safe. I have lots of energy and like playing with my toys. Please don’t leave your shoes around because I love those too. I don’t mind sleeping in a crate with my dog bed and blanket but my favorite time is to cuddle on the sofa with my human. I am not fully house trained, but I am trying really hard to do good, please have patience with me. I am good on the leash but do get nervous and don’t want to move at times. So you might have to nudge me a little. I love to be around other dogs and wouldn’t mind having a dog sibling. As another dog helps me to be more confident, then I am much more comfortable. I am good with children, but I might accidentally knock over a toddler as I love to play. I am such a snuggle bug, and truly love those I am around."

Lilly is about 10 months old and weighs 34 pounds. She is gorgeous and will make a wonderful new BFF ! She is healthy, up to date on her shots and is spayed. Lilly is currently in New England and can travel to her new home ASAP. Lilly would love to be with an active person and could live as the only dog or if you are trying to add another dog to your family. She is flexible!
Her adoption donation is $400 .

*Unless stated otherwise, all dogs will be spayed or neutered, on flea/tick product and heart worm prevention medicine (if older than 5 months) and micro chipped prior to adoption.

*Please note that while we do our best to accurately state the breed or breed mix of a dog, we often have very limited information to draw from. Identifying the breed without pedigrees and information on heritage can be very challenging!

If you are interested in adopting one of our animals, please go to www.angelsamongusanimalrescue.org and fill out an online adoption application. Thank you!

Massachusett's Residents: Effective September 28, 2017 a Quarantine Fee of $120 will be required  (in addition to the adoption fee) to adopt a dog that has been Quarantined. Massachusetts mandates that all dogs entering MA shall be quarantined for 48 hours in a state approved facility.

animal.description:
Micah recently lost his daddy through no fault of his own.   He has Perianal Fistulae and has been having a bit of a hard time.  He was with the same owner nearly all of his life over the past 8 years.   He’s been having problems coping with that loss.   He is undergoing treatment for his condition so we can get him as healthy as possible for adoption.
Micah was able to go to a foster home.  At first he was stressed and anxious and confused, but he came around and showed all the love he has to give.  He is friendly to small humans so far and seems less reactive to calm small dogs.  He does not seem to be a fan of dogs his size.   He’s a dream of a dog for the right family.   He walks well on a leash once he bonds to you but can be reactive to barking big dogs.
He will require a lifetime of management of his condition but he’s fantastic about allowing handling and easy to care for.  Once his condition is under control, it will be relatively simple to manage.

animal.description:
Hello!  Thank you for checking out Jimmy Smits' listing.  Please read carefully for details on our adoption process:
•First, please note that we are unable to receive correspondence through Petfinder’s system.  Any messages sent through Petfinder or any buttons on this listing will unfortunately not reach us. If you’re interested in adopting please visit www.sanctuaryrescue.com and submit an adoption questionnaire under the forms section.
• Applications are open until we will change the adoption listing to “Applications Closed”. Next, foster parents will contact approved applicants to set up a meet and greet. This can take up to 1 to 2 weeks.
• Once a dog is officially adopted we will remove its listing from Petfinder. So if this listing is gone, this dog has found its forever family and is no longer available.
• Since Covid lockdown orders, we have seen a massive increase in people interested in adopting dogs (yay!). This means each dog, especially puppies, receive multiple applications in the couple of days we have applications open. There is usually several applicants for one pup. If it doesn’t work out this time, please understand this is not a personal judgement but likely a result of supply and demand. We encourage you to reapply in the future.

Meet Smits! Smits is approximately two years old and weight under 10 lbs. Breed heritage is pure guess. He is working on crate training and basic commands. He likes other dogs but needs to work on boundaries and how to engage in play. He has met one cat during is time in rescue, he was interested but the cat was not. 

Smits would love a person or small family who wants a constant companion and a lap dog. Someone who is looking for a goofy friend to entertain them. Smits would like someone who enjoys daily walks that do not need to be strenuous. Smits is super sweet, funny, goofy little guy that is active but not hyper. He is a velcro dog who  loves to be on his person's lap a lot! 

Jimmy Smits' adoption fee is $250, which includes age-appropriate vaccinations, current on preventatives, neuter, and microchip. If you would like to make this handsome boy a part of your family, please visit sanctuaryrescue.com and complete an adoption questionnaire under the “Forms” tab.

animal.description:
Mama knows best when you feel down how to lift your heart .

Mama Ema Lou, well taken care of in her clean, gleaming 2 colored coat. Her tail wags with the fun when greeting her person and going out for a walk. Her leash manners are lovely, her tail wags as we walk, and she gives off such a pleasant 'vibe', if she catches a scent, you can give her a light tug . She loves to be petted and snuggled by her person, leaning in for better cuddles and all the while wagging her tail, That made her happy!! Chasing a tennis ball is just as much fun and she bounds after it bouncing it around. you can take it right out of her mouth for another throw and her tail wags more as she leaps after it. Shes an absolute doll!!! She was/is a very good mama but she is sooooo ready to be a puppy herself and be loved and shown direction/guidance/training so she can become her best self. Some good exercise, followed by some good snuggles....what could be better than that? Well, since you asked, it could be better if she were in her own home, surrounded by people who love her. She's an easy girl to love, so meet her and find out for yourself. With Mama by your side you'll have it all! She is potty and crate trained.

animal.description:
Sadie is a highly intelligent and energetic young Lab / Antolian Shepherd mix who is looking for an active family. Sadie is only one year old, but she is already fully housetrained, crate trained and knows many commands like bye bye, bed, look for/find it, and bring it! Not only does Sadie love to use her mind, but she also likes to stay physically active and would make an excellent agility, field or diving dog. Sadie doesn't realize her size and strengh; so while that means she thinks she fits perfectly cuddled up in a lap after a long day of adventures, it also means she would do best in a home with no small children. Sadie also has a high prey drive, so she needs to be in a home with no cats or small dogs.

The suggested adoption donation for Sadie is $400. We are a 501c3 organization which means that your donation may be TAX DEDUCTIBLE. Your donation goes toward the high cost of veterinary care for our animals in rescue, as well as providing supportive services to animals in homes.

Information about the adoption process: All adoptions require a completed ADOPTION APPLICATION. Once your application is approved, we will put you in touch with the dogs foster to see if you and the pet are a good match. If so, we will arrange a meeting for you and the pet. The adoptions for all of our animals will take place in the Omaha, NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver.

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dogs needs. If you and the dog are not a good match, we will help you select another dog, or we will keep your approved application on file for 6 months.

To learn about Muddy Paws Second Chance Rescue or donate to our animals, please visit our website at MuddyPawsSecondChanceRescue.com or our Facebook Page.

We are SO SORRY TO ADVISE YOU ... We are NO LONGER ADOPTING TO MASSACHUSETTS RESIDENTS DUE TO STRICTER AND UNATTAINABLE REGULATIONS !!

Arriving 2.20.2012  
Skipper is a 5 month old Dachshund (Beagle??)  mix that weighs 12 pounds. HE was found loitering around the town dumpsters and our volunteer , Daphanie scooped him up and took him home. 
After a warm meal, a warm bath and a soft bed, he looked a LOT better. 
We have since had all of his vetting tended to and he will be here 1/23/2021. He is energetic and "BUBBLY" Perhaps we SHOULD have called him Champagne - or per haps Prosecco! 
 He is only 5-6 months of age  and an absolute love-bug... Thanks to Mister Robinson for modeling!  
We think that he will only get 18-20 pounds as a full adult size! 

~~~~~

Due to Covid-19 concerns, we are not planning any public adoption events. If you are pre approved , we will call to set up an appointment to come and meet the dog and potentially take them home. It is by appointment only- 
Dogs will be brought into the outdoor kennel for you to meet and make your decision. MASKS WILL BE MANDATORY to maintain EVERYONE'S safety  NO EXCEPTIONS PLEASE !! Unless otherwise noted, the puppies and dogs listed will arrive on Saturday, January 23rd 2021 .
Please follow this link to fill out an application. It is step one in adopting a pup from our rescue.
http://littlerhodyrescue.com/adoption-application/ 
 

*Filling an application does not guarantee you as the adopter. All applicant's references will be called. PLEASE call your veterinarian and personal references and allow consent to speaking with us ! 
We cannot process your application otherwise. Failure will put your application in 'Limbo"  
We process applications as they arrive. The first approved applicant will be called and the pup taken off of Petfinder. We do not have the man/ woman power to all all other applicants to advise them. 
IF there s another dog that you are interested in as well, please list at the top of the application and we will enter your application for that pup if the first choice has been adopted. 

THANK YOU !!! You are giving a first rate dog a second chance....By adopting! 

***** SADLY , we need to put this in print: THIS IS A RESCUE DOG. We do NOT know their birthday / age.  (unless other wise noted)  
More often than not, OUR TEAM  has saved them from euthanasia in Southern shelters. 
We do not know any more than our Veterinarians offer to us. 
 We often have them in kennels, and utilize crate training.  House training status is often NOT KNOWN. 
Prior Health, estimated weight  (as an adult), breed (Including the parents' breed , size or mix)   and some health concerns are  NOT KNOWN unless our veterinarians discover it and offer the information to us.   Again, these are strays and turn ins from all over the country. They do NOT come with labels; nor guarantees. 

Characteristics and disposition can and will evolve with time.
YOU the adopter are responsible to train and keep up to date on vaccines and preventatives.  
YOU the adopter are responsible for taking care of this new member of your family. 
 *************

****
Our adoption fees are $ 600. This fee includes the transportation of the pet from one of the organizations that we work with in TX, LA or TN. Before joining us in RI all dogs are: spayed/neutered, microchipped, up to date on age-appropriate vaccines, and on de-wormers, flea/tick and heartworm prevention. In addition, all adults (6 months +) are heartworm tested and MUST be negative for both heartworm and microfilaria before transport. 

In addition to the above, all dogs must have a Certificate of Veterinary Inspection and be deemed healthy per USDA law in order to travel. Once they have been certified they are then transported via USDA transport services only, which is required by law. 
 We  sometimes don't understand how bad the situation is for these pups and dogs in southern states.  Many people in the south don't spay or neuter their pets as we do here. Subsequently, there are thousands of beautiful , worthy pups and dogs, kittens and cats  that are dumped, shot, abandoned, brought into shelters, neglected, abused and abandoned.  We step in , tend to their veterinary needs. As you can see above, we never fail to properly spay and neuter. Everything is done with the  caring , capable hands of our veterinarians to get them healthy and ready to place them for adoption. That's when we put the demand for family- friendly pets with the supply ..... 

Give a first rate dog a second chance!!!! ADOPT! 


Keep in mind that we also offer a two week return policy for the return of a healthy dog that includes a full refund. We want to make sure that the adoption is a perfect fit for both you and the dog.

If you would like more information about adopting please select "More About Little Rhody Rescue" where you will also find our online application if you'd like to proceed with the adoption process. Thank you!

animal.description:
Hi there!  My name is MILO.  What’s yours?  Nice to meet ya!  

WATCH MY VIDEO:  https://youtu.be/C6OmmW1qWzY

https://youtu.be/7j6NvJyryLo

A nice person came along and took me in and, now, I am ready to hit the road to your house!  Uh, make that “our” house, OK?  I definitely need a house with a fenced-in yard cuz I need room to run and romp and be safe!  The rescue requires (1) a fenced-in yard and (2) a vet reference from a vet that you have used for a current or previous dog to be sure that all vetting was done and (3) a comparable-sized doggie sibling)  

I am a Retriever/Staffy mix.  I am 10 MONTHS old and I weigh 55-60 pounds. I have been neutered and am up to date on vaccines so I'm ready to go to my new home with YOU!!  Those funny-looking 2-legged creatures said I’m also microchipped – whatever THAT is.  At any rate, I am fully vetted.  Is that anything close to petted?  I love to be petted!  They say I'm precious.  Hmmm, Is my name Milo or Precious?

Wanna hear some more good stuff about me?  OK, here goes.  I like ALL people and ALL dogs.  I need to have a DOGGIE SIBLING about my size so we can run and romp together and burn up LOTS and LOTS of energy!   I know basic commands.  I respond very well to consistent, positive reinforcement training and I'm a good learner!  Smart, huh?

I am attentive, affectionate, silly, playful and loyal.  I LOVE cuddles, car rides, holding hands and tummy rubs.  I am a beta doggie.  I back down when prompted by aggressive dogs. I'm an amazing companion!

I have lots to learn.  Will you teach me all the things a pup needs to know to be safe and happy? I LOVE to give kisses so get ready!  

If you have children, then need to be older children - 12 and up because I like to play hard and run fast!  It's fun!

I like to take naps when I'm tired from playing.  I need  love, exercise and couch-sitting when we get tired!  Let's be a team, OK?

If you would like to take me home (and you know you do), please email rescuedogsgalore@gmail.com  and they can get me on my way to a new and loving home!  Once you adopt me, I will be flown to Seattle from Houston, TX.  (Seattle is the only place we can fly to right now.)  My adoption fee is $450 and includes my vetting, neutering, flight cost, travel crate, Health Certificate and a microchip.

animal.description:
Teddy Bear Bruce is now available for adoption! <3

"Bruce is an oversized puppy. He is playful, he is curious, he has spurts of energy, and he seems to be looking at the world through new eyes. I don't think he was ever part of a family before coming to us. He has scratches across his nose that we fear may have been from a fight with some wild animal. He also has scabs on his body and head. They have healed nicely, but this boy has been through something. He came to us a rambunctious puppy. He wanted to play with other dogs, he was food crazy, and he had manners to learn. In the almost week he has been with us, he has settled in nicely. 
Bruce is starting to try and play with the other dogs. You can tell he never has before. He plays rough, but the other dogs are teaching him how to play. He sometimes gets so excited he turns into a jumping fool and barks around. He has so much life in him, and is learning how to be a dog again. It is really fun to watch him come around. To watch the light return to his eyes. To watch him learn what having a family feels like. He still has some manners to learn, but that is what comes with having a rescue dog. He knew nothing and has come so far in the few days we have had him. 
Bruce is potty trained, good with other dogs, and has good house manners. Right now, he just wants to be with his people and will jump up at the door and whine when his people leave. He settles down shortly after, though. He LOVES attention and will lean against you so much you think he will fall over. He loves giving you this big ole grin that will melt your heart. He also has the head tilt down to a T. This dog will steal you heart, let me tell you. If you know big dogs, you will understand this boy is all puppy still. He didn't get to just have fun. He didn't get to have a carefree life, but he sure is getting to now! With some more training, this guy will be the most amazing family member. He just has this aura around him that draws you in, and before you know it...he has stolen your heart." 

I showed up as a stray to the shelter. It is pretty scary to not have anyone. No one came for me. No one adopted me. No one seemed to want me. And why I don't know why. I wanted a home so bad. Then, something did happen. A rescue stepped up for me. Before I knew it, I was in a foster home and my life flipped. I got to come inside the house, which was a totally new concept. There were other dogs around, and I was so excited to play with them. Now that I have settled in, I am ready to search for my forever family! My name is Bruce and I am a 2 year old male Great Pyrenees/Anatolian mix. I currently weigh about 72lbs, and will top out close to the 85-90lb range. I believe my coat is going to come in thicker as well. 

My Personality: 
I am a mix of calm and playful. If the other dogs are excited, I get super excited. If everyone is calm, I am pretty calm too. I tend to match the energy of my family. I am indifferent when it comes to meeting new people. I would rather explore my surroundings. I have not been to any public outings, but figure I would be excited to check out my surroundings. I don't seem to be interested in playing fetch. I am unsure if I am a water dog or not. I am unsure of what toys are right now, but my fosters think I will start playing with them soon. I was pretty crazy about food when I first came into rescue. I have settled down since, and am fine as long as another dog doesn't try taking my treat/food. I don't seem to have any issues with resource guarding. I don't seem to be much of a jumper/hugger with people. I do load up pretty easy in the car. Once in, I tend to just lay down and chill. I do walk well on a leash, but may pull some. Especially if there is something I want to check out. 

I am good with other dogs. I am learning to play with them, and can be a bit rough at times. I run/jump around them trying to get them to play. My fosters dogs are teaching me the proper way to play, but I definitely need a playmate my size. I would be too rambunctious for a smaller dog. I am okay with cats, but will give chase if they run. I have not been around any kids. Since I am rowdy at times, the kiddos should be 12+. 

My House Manners: 
I am a big ole puppy. I am curious about things and like to explore the house. I have not attempted to chew on anything I shouldn't. I am pretty excitable still and don't believe I would be a good candidate for apartment living. I can be vocal when I get excited or hear other dogs barking. When no one is home, I am given free roam of the house. At night, I sleep downstairs. I am potty trained. I am NOT kennel trained, though. I panic in a kennel and need a home that won't kennel me. 

To My New Family: 

-I am looking for a home that has at least one other playful dog my size. 

-I would love a family that is home most of the day. 

-I am looking for a home that won't kennel me. I panic in one. I know some dogs see it as their safe place, but I don't. 

If you are looking for a big ole puppy/teddy bear than I am totally the boy for you. I am a playful and loving guy looking to find his place in this world. https://www.pyrpawsandfluffytailsrescue.com/adoption-app 

My adoption fee is $225. That includes my DHLPP, Rabies, and Bordatella shots. I will be micro-chipped, heart-worm tested, ehrlichia tested, have a fecal done, be de-wormed, be spayed/neutered and will be current on my heart-worm and flea/tick prevention.

Lastly, I am being fostered in Kiowa, OK. I have no qualms about going out of state if my adopters don't live in Oklahoma. All I ask is they come pick me up. Those transports are too stressful and this rescue doesn't put us on those or ship us.

Breed:  Formosan Mountain Dog mix
Age: 7 months
Weight:  18 lbs.
Good with dogs:  yes
Good with cats:  unsure
