Energy level:  high
Good with men/strangers:  yes
Hypoallergenic:  no

Special home requirements or medical:  no kids under 12 yrs.; needs secure yard with a quiet home in a quiet neighborhood; flight risk

Additional info:

Shy little Cato is adjusting well to being in his foster home.   He is a blank slate and does need some basic training. He is full of life inside the home, loves to play and adores his person but is a little skittish and timid when on walks and hears loud noises. He has lots of energy so is looking for a home that is active and has another playful dog. He still has a lot of his young puppy traits and when he gets bored, will find something interesting to chew on.   He is working on crate training so he can understand boundaries. Cato needs a home that has the time to work with him to help him adjust to the outside world more and burn his energy. He is highly treat motivated which comes in handy.   He will be an amazing dog once he gets some structure and routine.

INTERESTED IN THIS PUP? If you want to know if the puppy is still available- we advise you to go ahead and apply which will free us up to review your application. We thank you for your patience. Our inbox gets flooded with so many puppy requests it takes us longer to respond.

If you are not ready to adopt just yet and would like to help in other ways, please consider clicking on the green “Sponsor Me” button above to help this dog receive the best care we can give. We rely on the generosity of others to make rescuing dogs possible.

IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN ADOPTING THIS DOG, PLEASE MAKE SURE YOU HAVE READ THE DOG'S INFORMATION CAREFULLY.  ONCE YOU HAVE DONE SO, PLEASE DO THE FOLLOWING:
1.       Visit www.dogswithoutborders.org
2.      Then fill out an online ADOPTION APPLICATION -  http://dogswithoutborders.org/adopt-a-dog/adoption-application/
3.       Please wait to hear from our representative in approximately 48 hours on weekdays.
4.       To learn more about our adoption process, please look up our Adoption FAQ’s. - http://dogswithoutborders.org/adopt-a-dog/adoption-faq/

animal.description:
Well hello, my name is Hannah. I was saved from New Mexico a few months back with my 5 month old puppy. I ended up being pregnant again (surprise!) and had 6 more adorable babies. They have all found their homes and now its my turn. When I first came into rescue I was really scared and shy. I was also very protective of my babies, so it made it difficult to work on socializing me. But the past few weeks I've really been coming out of my shell. Turns out I LOVE dogs! I love to play chase, and wrestle - I have a fairly rough and rowdy playstyle with another dog that plays the same way - but also tone it down and just throw playbows at the more mellow dogs. I prefer female humans, but am learning that the male ones aren't too bad either (as long as they have lots of treats). I am very food motivated which is helpful. I am trusted loose in the house, and am a really good girl inside, I usually just sit and stare out the window. But then as soon as we go outside, playtime is on! I'm looking for a loving home that will be patient with me as I continue learning and socializing. Another friendly dog my size would be great too! 

https://www.facebook.com/thegooddogrescue/videos/1844508895705399

Due to the current events, the rescue is not able to host adoption events.  Please fill out an application and we will conduct phone interviews and set up outdoor meet and greets! www.thegooddogrescue.org

My adoption fee is $250 and I will be spayed, microchipped and up to date on vaccinations prior to adoption

animal.description:
~~~~~
Uno is a 3 month old Maltese Chihuahua mix- she her mom (Maltese) and her siblings came into the local shelter in Louisiana ALL of them had Canine Parvo virus.  A deadly horrible virus whose morbidity is extremely high. 
She is only of the only survivors. Momma never made it , either.  So a bottle feeding we will go! They were lucky - at such a small size and young age; many won't make it. 

at any rate, they survived and are here to tell the tale !  Fill out an application if you are interested?? 
LittleRhodyrescue.com

~~~~~

Due to Covid-19 concerns, we are not planning any public adoption events. If you are pre approved , we will call to set up an appointment to come and meet the dog and potentially take them home. It is by appointment only- 
Dogs will be brought into the outdoor kennel for you to meet and make your decision. MASKS WILL BE MANDATORY to maintain EVERYONE'S safety  NO EXCEPTIONS PLEASE !! Unless otherwise noted, the puppies and dogs listed will arrive on Saturday, January 23rd 2021 .
Please follow this link to fill out an application. It is step one in adopting a pup from our rescue.
http://littlerhodyrescue.com/adoption-application/ 
 

*Filling an application does not guarantee you as the adopter. All applicant's references will be called. PLEASE call your veterinarian and personal references and allow consent to speaking with us ! 
We cannot process your application otherwise. Failure will put your application in 'Limbo"  
We process applications as they arrive. The first approved applicant will be called and the pup taken off of Petfinder. We do not have the man/ woman power to all all other applicants to advise them. 
IF there s another dog that you are interested in as well, please list at the top of the application and we will enter your application for that pup if the first choice has been adopted. 

THANK YOU !!! You are giving a first rate dog a second chance....By adopting! 

***** SADLY , we need to put this in print: THIS IS A RESCUE DOG. We do NOT know their birthday / age.  (unless other wise noted)  
More often than not, OUR TEAM  has saved them from euthanasia in Southern shelters. 
We do not know any more than our Veterinarians offer to us. 
 We often have them in kennels, and utilize crate training.  House training status is often NOT KNOWN. 
Prior Health, estimated weight  (as an adult), breed (Including the parents' breed , size or mix)   and some health concerns are  NOT KNOWN unless our veterinarians discover it and offer the information to us.   Again, these are strays and turn ins from all over the country. They do NOT come with labels; nor guarantees. 

Characteristics and disposition can and will evolve with time.
YOU the adopter are responsible to train and keep up to date on vaccines and preventatives.  
YOU the adopter are responsible for taking care of this new member of your family. 
 *************

****
Our adoption fees are $ 600. This fee includes the transportation of the pet from one of the organizations that we work with in TX, LA or TN. Before joining us in RI all dogs are: spayed/neutered, microchipped, up to date on age-appropriate vaccines, and on de-wormers, flea/tick and heartworm prevention. In addition, all adults (6 months +) are heartworm tested and MUST be negative for both heartworm and microfilaria before transport. 

In addition to the above, all dogs must have a Certificate of Veterinary Inspection and be deemed healthy per USDA law in order to travel. Once they have been certified they are then transported via USDA transport services only, which is required by law. 
 We  sometimes don't understand how bad the situation is for these pups and dogs in southern states.  Many people in the south don't spay or neuter their pets as we do here. Subsequently, there are thousands of beautiful , worthy pups and dogs, kittens and cats  that are dumped, shot, abandoned, brought into shelters, neglected, abused and abandoned.  We step in , tend to their veterinary needs. As you can see above, we never fail to properly spay and neuter. Everything is done with the  caring , capable hands of our veterinarians to get them healthy and ready to place them for adoption. That's when we put the demand for family- friendly pets with the supply ..... 

Give a first rate dog a second chance!!!! ADOPT! 


Keep in mind that we also offer a two week return policy for the return of a healthy dog that includes a full refund. We want to make sure that the adoption is a perfect fit for both you and the dog.

If you would like more information about adopting please select "More About Little Rhody Rescue" where you will also find our online application if you'd like to proceed with the adoption process. Thank you!

animal.description:
"Trek" is around 2 years old, a Mountain Cur and Pit mix, around 45 pounds.  Neutered, vaccinated and heartworm tested.  He gets along with other dogs, is probably too big for small children but older, respectful kids would be fine.  NO cats!
Trek was surrendered by his owner because she allowed him to roam the neighborhood and she was going to start getting citations for a dog at large.  Trek came into animal control fearful and aggressive.  The animal control officer worked with him and after several days, he showed his true colors....a big playful softie.  Trek is in a foster home now and has been a joy to have around.  He's housebroken and gentle.  Walks nicely on a leash and is getting along very well with another much smaller foster dog.  No problems with meeting new people while on walks.  Not pesky when you're trying to eat and he takes treats gently.  Was cooperative getting a bath, even though he really didn't like it much!  If you'd like to have a meet 'n greet with Trek call Friends of Horseshoe Bend Animals at 870-373-2649 or shoot us a message.  Adoption fee is $30.

animal.description:
Tazzy was found alone in an apartment complex in December 2020. I took her in to foster her. She is young, very playful, and she is teething at the moment. She does not like to be loved on too much, she thinks she is independent. She also does not like to be alone. I have other dogs and cats that she likes to play with and be around. Taz likes to chase my cats around the house, she is learning her boundaries with them. Taz sleeps well in her kennel, but she does not like to be in it when she is not asleep.

Tazzy is available for foster to adopt in the Greater Houston area only. Apply at hhfrescue.org.The adoption fee includes vaccinations, bordetella, deworming, rabies, spay/neuter, microchip, a lifetime registration of the microchip, and sales tax. If adopting a puppy, the rabies and spay/neuter will be done at the same time by our vet once they are 4 months old and billed to us. It is against the law in the State of Texas for a rescue not to be sterilized so we have to make sure it gets completed and that we have record of it.

animal.description:
Snapshot of Cinnabon Delight!

Size?
I'm a puppy still growing

Age? 3 months
Activity Level?
I like to play hard!

Noise Level?
I like to bark when I play!

Good with Dogs? I need slow intros and space!
Good with Cats? I like them more than they like me! (
Dog-savvy cats may be okay)

Good with Kids? I love little ones!
Good with Strangers?
I need slow intros and space!

Potty Trained?
I'm a puppy so I'm still learning!

Crate Trained?
I bark some, but quiet down quickly!

Interested? Learn more about Cinnabon Delight below!

About Cinnabon Delight:

My name is Cinnabon Delight! I am a 3 month old Lab mix. I'm sweet, playful, curious, and active. I'm working on my potty training. I usually go to the door and make it outside in time. I'm comfortable sleeping in my crate, but I don't want to be in there if there's fun to be had! Recently, I got the chance to meet some other dogs. I was timid and shy when I first met them, but once I had some time and space, it was a lot of fun! I have met a family cat, and we had a lot of time figuring each other out. But it seems like I like her more than she likes me! My foster mom taught me to sit and stay, and I've gotten really good at it! She has me do it before going out and before my meals. I have started to walk on a leash and am getting better each time! I am a puppy and still learning to come. I love playing with my foster mom and her daughter, they both play games with me and let me run after they throw my toys around. After a long day, I like to snuggle up!

Adoption Fee: $550

Training Requirement: Obedience Training Level 1

*Foster to Adopt: I am looking for a forever home now, but I still need all my puppy shots and to be spayed! So I'm looking for a family that will be able to commit to bringing me to all of my appointments with TCPR until I'm ready to be fully adopted by you!

MEET ME/ADOPT ME: If you'd like to arrange a meeting or begin the adoption process, please fill out an adoption application by visiting www.twincitiespetrescue.org/adopt/adopt-a-dog/ . A volunteer from Twin Cities Pet Rescue will contact you once your application is reviewed.

FOSTER HOMES NEEDED!!! Twin Cities Pet Rescue is a volunteer-run, foster home-based organization. We can only rescue as many animals as available foster homes. Please consider saving the life of an animal in need and become a volunteer foster home today. To become a foster, fill out a dog or cat foster application on the Twin Cities Pet Rescue website: www.twincitiespetrescue.org . There is little to no cost to foster an animal. Twin Cities Pet Rescue provides its foster families with food, supplies, and veterinary care for its animals. All you need to do is supply the love!

PLEASE NOTE: Twin Cities Pet Rescue does not adopt to homes further than 60 miles from the Minneapolis/St. Paul Metro Area.
